1
00:00:00,120 --> 00:00:01,480
Let's make a deal.

2
00:00:01,520 --> 00:00:04,760
Fighting is my job and cooking is yours.

3
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:05,760
Do you hear me?

4
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:08,760
You're the lady of
the house, you'll cook the meals.

5
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:10,119
Is that so?

6
00:00:10,120 --> 00:00:14,080
Why would
I, is there a law that says I have to cook?

7
00:00:15,040 --> 00:00:16,320
We're equals in this house.

8
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:19,680
If I were you, I'd go and spoil their fun.

9
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,080
You're not well, you know.

10
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:23,360
I'm telling you they're
staying the night there.

11
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:24,719
Just the two of them.

12
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:26,999
Why is no one listening to me?

13
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,880
Could it be
because you're being ridiculous?

14
00:00:30,360 --> 00:00:32,440
Don't you dare try to hurt Mercan,

15
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:34,920
or I'll kill you.

16
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:40,360
I won't let you take what's mine.

17
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:49,960
But this is the ring Nezir bought.

18
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:52,600
What are you looking at so intently?

19
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:58,320
Who put this trash in our room?

20
00:00:58,840 --> 00:01:00,280
Why are you asking us?

21
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:03,400
She must have kept it
as a souvenir from her engagement to Nezir.

22
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:04,520
Aslı!

23
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:06,880
Wasn't she engaged to that man?

24
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:09,200
The ring must be theirs.

25
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:10,960
Mercan didn't keep keep this.

26
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:13,840
You said he wouldn't even want to
look at her after this.

27
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:17,040
They've already established trust
between them.

28
00:01:17,360 --> 00:01:20,480
She's taking the man
I love from me right in front of our eyes.

29
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:22,240
I'll kill that girl.

30
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:23,840
Everyone should hear it.

31
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:26,360
Enough, I've had enough!

32
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:30,760
He acted as though he
was actually her husband.

33
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:32,960
He must have fallen for our daughter.

34
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,880
What are you talking about, Nermin?

35
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:36,160
Mercan.

36
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:37,760
We'll find her, right?

37
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,520
I will never upset her again.

38
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:43,120
Something like this doesn't have to happen
just so we learn not to upset each other.

39
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:45,720
You're right.

40
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:51,440
Something terrible happened because
you took this marriage thing too seriously.

41
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:55,319
You protected Mercan against us but,

42
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:58,440
she's dismissing you completely and seeing
Nezir behind your back.

43
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:00,560
Mom, you're stepping out of line.

44
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:02,160
See for yourself.

45
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:08,680
Ateş.

46
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,160
What are you doing with this man?

47
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,840
I asked you what you're doing here!

48
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:44,160
I was just looking for Demet...

49
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:45,319
Ateş.

50
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:46,800
It's not what you think.

51
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:48,640
We can explain.

52
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:52,520
What do you mean
by what he thinks? What are you saying?

53
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:04,920
Ateş, don't!

54
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:10,160
Ateş won't
even look at your face from now on.

55
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,560
What are you doing?

56
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:15,360
Don't say another word! Get in the car.

57
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:18,720
What are you doing? Why are you acting like
this?

58
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:19,840
I said get in the car.

59
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:58,640
See?
It's really over for you this time, Mercan.

60
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:29,400
I don't understand why
you're acting like this.

61
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:32,000
What were you doing at Nezir's house?

62
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:38,400
I
Said what were you doing at Nezir's house!

63
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:44,760
I didn't go in, I was outside. I went there
looking for Demet.

64
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:47,120
Is this your explanation?

65
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,080
You went looking for Demet.

66
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,440
That man was embracing you.

67
00:05:57,640 --> 00:05:59,776
He was feeling dizzy, he was worried about
his sister.

68
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:00,520
That's why.

69
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,640
I said that man was embracing you!

70
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:07,040
And you?

71
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:10,000
How could you touch him?

72
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:18,760
Why were you looking for Demet?

73
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:23,360
We couldn't
reach her. I was really worried about her.

74
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:24,920
Ateş, listen.

75
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:26,400
Why didn't you go alone?

76
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:29,200
Why did you with him, then?

77
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:33,800
I
Didn't go with him, Nezir showed up later.

78
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:37,120
What's up with
these questions? What's going on?

79
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:39,680
Why didn't you let me know?

80
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:41,360
I called you.

81
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:43,800
No.

82
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,199
You didn't.

83
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,280
I did.

84
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,320
I called multiple times, you didn't answer.

85
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:54,400
What's this?

86
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:03,880
Listen...

87
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:07,760
I left it on silent, I'd
meant to let you know.

88
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,040
Okay, I get it.

89
00:07:11,041 --> 00:07:13,680
You got worried because you couldn't reach
me, I understand.

90
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:15,040
But I...

91
00:07:15,041 --> 00:07:17,040
So you got together with Nezir to

92
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,200
look for Demet.

93
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:24,200
Forget about it.

94
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:27,480
Why was
that man embracing you? Tell me about that.

95
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:30,040
He wasn't embracing me.

96
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:32,160
He was dizzy, so, he held on to me and I

97
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,960
helped him. What's so wrong about that?

98
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:37,240
Why do you care about his dizziness, what's
it to you!?

99
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:41,640
Are you not listening to me at all?

100
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:45,320
He was dizzy and worried about his sister.

101
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:49,280
I'm going to lose it.

102
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:50,720
I'm going to lose my mind!

103
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:53,240
So, he was dizzy.

104
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:58,920
Wait a minute.

105
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:02,520
Hold on. Are you trying
to insinuate something, yet again?

106
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:06,960
If you're even thinking
of something like that...

107
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,080
Don't you dare.

108
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:11,400
Don't you dare do something like that to me
again, do you hear me?

109
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:14,480
What else do you expect me to think?

110
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:17,440
Don't you dare.

111
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:20,400
Don't you dare treat me
like I'm lying to you.

112
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:31,360
Give me one reason why
I should believe you.

113
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:35,600
One single reason.

114
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:42,440
Look at me.

115
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,080
Look into my eyes. Look deep.

116
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:48,280
It's me. It's me, Mercan!

117
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:51,640
I don't need
to tell you anything else, do you hear me?

118
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,560
You already know.

119
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:59,360
There are things I won't put up with, know
your limit.

120
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,840
You too.

121
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:16,200
Because this will have
serious consequences.

122
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,280
What do you mean by that?

123
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,520
What consequences?

124
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:24,600
What will you do?

125
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,800
Will you send me away again?

126
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:30,080
Will you call off the
deal, what will you do?

127
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:34,080
Or will you divorce me, huh?

128
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:36,399
Tell
me, will you divorce me, what will you do?

129
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,800
Come on, tell me.

130
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:40,040
Will you divorce me?

131
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:50,080
It's not broken, is it?

132
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:52,280
No, it's not. Don't worry.

133
00:10:53,160 --> 00:10:54,960
You couldn't stand the
pain if it was broken.

134
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,680
You're in a better mood.

135
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:02,240
Kind of. We didn't
exactly get what we wanted but still.

136
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:04,840
Even this much was enough.

137
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:08,240
Ateş will never forgive that snake.

138
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:10,640
Watch your mouth, Aslı.

139
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:14,840
I'm sorry
but that girl is a sneaky snake in my eyes.

140
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:17,720
I'm not going to hide my feelings
just because you're in love with her.

141
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:20,800
Mercan couldn't beat you in sneakiness.

142
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:21,720
What about you?

143
00:11:21,721 --> 00:11:24,400
I don't think you're in
any position to make that comment.

144
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:25,840
You sound ridiculous.

145
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:29,440
So?

146
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:31,880
What now?

147
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,320
What's next?

148
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:37,160
You and your mom came
up with this game plan.

149
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:40,200
Maybe we won't have to do anything else.

150
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,600
Maybe Ateş will let her go.

151
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:45,840
What if he doesn't?

152
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:49,960
Then we'll keep Ateş' rage alive.

153
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:55,120
We can never let that sneaky snake convince
Ateş.

154
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:56,800
Don't forget,

155
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:59,680
my mom and
I are not the only ones who made this game.

156
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,760
You're a part of this.

157
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:05,840
There are three of us.

158
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,160
Come on, let's go.

159
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:13,720
You'll wipe your nose in the car, come on.

160
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,920
I'm going to lose my mind.

161
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:06,080
They muddied our name while we were trying
to ruin their reputation.

162
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,720
Can we talk later?

163
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:15,840
Even if it's just on paper she's your wife,
Ateş!

164
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:18,160
Mom.

165
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:20,080
Please stop talking.

166
00:14:20,640 --> 00:14:24,160
Her going to some strange man's house
to sleep around is unacceptable!

167
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:25,800
Mom!

168
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:28,000
That's enough!

169
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:29,800
Leave me alone.

170
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:33,640
Are you going to let them muddy our name?

171
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:37,640
Enough!

172
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:53,040
You'll keep beating yourself up if you keep
going like this.

173
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,200
Mom.

174
00:14:58,160 --> 00:15:00,120
Mom, please don't send me away.

175
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:01,879
I don't want to go.

176
00:15:01,880 --> 00:15:04,560
I don't want to be away
from you or my brother.

177
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:06,959
Is it
us you don't want to be away from or Malik?

178
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:08,800
What are you saying, mom?

179
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:15,080
The two of you staying in this house is not
appropriate anymore.

180
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,480
One of you need to leave.

181
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:19,160
Why? Why do we have to go?

182
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,719
It has to be that way.

183
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:24,319
Since I can't tell
a stranger to pack up and leave this house,

184
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:25,760
it'd be more reasonable if you left.

185
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,000
But why?

186
00:15:28,560 --> 00:15:31,199
Do you think
I have the energy to follow you two around?

187
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:34,560
Mom, please don't
hurt me like this, I'm begging you.

188
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:38,040
I'm not hurting you, Çiçek. I'm doing this
for your own good.

189
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:41,520
Mom, please don't push
me away like this, I'm begging you.

190
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:46,839
I'm protecting you from a future mistake.

191
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:47,800
Do you understand?

192
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:49,800
This is how you protect me?

193
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:54,720
You're protecting me by distancing me from
people I love?

194
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:59,799
You need to go away for
a while to pull yourself together, Çiçek.

195
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:00,920
Do you hear me?

196
00:17:24,120 --> 00:17:25,160
Come in.

197
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,520
Where have you been?
We've been worried sick about you.

198
00:17:36,120 --> 00:17:37,239
I'm really sorry.

199
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:40,200
You went to the summer
house looking for me,

200
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:43,119
Nezir told me about it.

201
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:45,080
Ateş went mad again, didn't he?

202
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:46,600
He did.

203
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:48,360
Really mad.

204
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,880
It's all because of me.

205
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:51,959
I couldn't find my phone, so I went home to
look for it.

206
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,080
I thought I'd left it there.

207
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:55,080
All hell broke loose while I was gone.

208
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,920
Nezir said you weren't home.

209
00:17:58,240 --> 00:18:00,200
I
Didn't go straight home, that must be why.

210
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,840
You got upset for no reason.

211
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:07,040
I don't understand how
things escalated this far.

212
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:10,960
Ateş misunderstood everything.

213
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:14,920
That man almost broke my brother's nose.

214
00:18:15,920 --> 00:18:17,560
He didn't do anything to you, did he?

215
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:19,600
No.

216
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:21,320
He wouldn't hurt me.

217
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:24,800
But he doesn't
believe that I went there looking for you.

218
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:26,680
Forget about him.

219
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:28,240
Let him believe whatever he wants.

220
00:18:30,320 --> 00:18:33,840
But I mean,
he's right in a sense if you think about it

221
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:37,320
He called multiple times and couldn't reach
me,

222
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:39,880
and
then, seeing me at your house like that...

223
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:43,440
Do you have
any obligation to convince him of anything?

224
00:18:44,520 --> 00:18:46,760
He's not going to be in your life for very
long, anyway.

225
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:49,920
That doesn't matter.

226
00:18:51,040 --> 00:18:53,040
I don't want him to think badly of me.

227
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:56,320
And things had just started to look up...

228
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:00,440
What's going on, Mercan?

229
00:19:01,720 --> 00:19:04,960
You didn't care about
being misunderstood by him before.

230
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:07,959
There's nothing going on.

231
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:09,000
What would there be?

232
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:12,080
I just
don't want to be misunderstood, that's all.

233
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:14,560
I got that much but,

234
00:19:15,760 --> 00:19:17,160
I don't understand why.

235
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:23,280
Ateş is not a bad person.

236
00:19:24,320 --> 00:19:26,000
We've been through a lot together.

237
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:29,800
I
Don't know why either, maybe out of habit,

238
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:34,400
but I think even if our marriage is just a
formality,

239
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:37,160
it was wrong of me to
go to another man's house.

240
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,080
I'm angry with myself.

241
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:45,520
Also, do you think he
may be overly protective of you?

242
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:53,880
If you want, I can
talk to him about this situation.

243
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:55,240
No.

244
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:56,839
It'd only be right if I talked to him.

245
00:19:56,840 --> 00:20:01,000
Even if he's right, he
should've believed me.

246
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:03,720
I'll be right back.

247
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:04,560
I should go, anyway.

248
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:07,040
I don't want Nezir to
blow things out of proportion again.

249
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:09,000
Okay, let's go.

250
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:33,120
Take this.

251
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:37,560
What's this?

252
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:41,440
The
money you paid the loan sharks in my place.

253
00:20:42,960 --> 00:20:44,440
Where did you get this money?

254
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:47,760
Berat? You didn't do anything wrong again,
did you?

255
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:49,400
What's it to you?

256
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:51,000
Huh?

257
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:53,320
It's none of your business, do you hear me?

258
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:56,960
Take it. I've paid off
my debt to you, we've squared our account.

259
00:20:57,640 --> 00:21:00,200
Don't be ridiculous. That was never a loan.

260
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:03,520
Malik, I told you to take this.

261
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:04,720
Okay?

262
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:06,360
Berat, don't do this.

263
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:08,480
We're friends.

264
00:21:09,040 --> 00:21:10,120
We're not.

265
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:14,760
We're not friends. From now on, I
don't want any good deed or money from you.

266
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:16,279
Do you hear me?

267
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:18,200
You will stay away from my sister,

268
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:20,040
or else, Malik.

269
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:22,200
Berat, I have infinite respect for you.

270
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:24,239
But don't ask me that one thing.

271
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:25,800
I can't turn my back on Çiçek.

272
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:49,359
You still dare say her name!

273
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:51,880
How dare you still say Çiçek, Malik!

274
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:58,039
From now on, I won't see you around Çiçek.

275
00:21:58,040 --> 00:21:59,360
Do you hear me?

276
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:04,840
I would never hit you back even if you hit
me a thousand times.

277
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:09,240
I can't ever hurt you or give up Çiçek.

278
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:13,120
Malik.

279
00:22:14,040 --> 00:22:15,200
Malik.

280
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:23,160
Even if the ground I stand on breaks apart,
even if the world collapses in on itself,

281
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,880
I will never give Çiçek up.

282
00:22:55,760 --> 00:22:58,920
"Give me one reason why
I should believe you."

283
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:05,240
Look at me. Look
into my eyes. Look deep. Do you see?

284
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:07,240
It's me. It's me, Mercan!

285
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:10,520
I don't need
to tell you anything else, do you hear me?

286
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:58,160
Can we talk for a moment?

287
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:06,480
Please?

288
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:18,920
What are you doing?

289
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:20,640
What if I hit you?

290
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:22,600
I'd protect myself.

291
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:27,160
Let's talk.

292
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:30,040
I don't want to talk.

293
00:24:35,320 --> 00:24:36,720
I want to work out, too.

294
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:42,440
I haven'tin a while.

295
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:52,440
I said I don't want to talk, what don't you
understand?

296
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:57,160
We'll talk.

297
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:09,000
You're right.

298
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:10,920
It's my fault.

299
00:25:14,040 --> 00:25:15,560
I should've called you first.

300
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:20,280
But in that moment, I
was prideful and angry.

301
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:26,400
I was mad
at you for what you said to me in the car.

302
00:25:27,240 --> 00:25:29,280
But now, I'm mad at myself.

303
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:41,160
Are you not coming?

304
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:43,720
I have some business.

305
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:46,440
What business?

306
00:25:47,360 --> 00:25:48,520
Are you interrogating me?

307
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:53,480
Since when do we let each other know where
we're going?

308
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:55,360
Am I missing something?

309
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:05,680
It's all because of you!

310
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:08,560
If you hadn't made me mad I would've let

311
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:10,520
you know
and none of this would've happened.

312
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:11,880
But it did.

313
00:26:18,280 --> 00:26:20,120
I don't want us to be on bad terms.

314
00:26:21,560 --> 00:26:23,120
You should've thought of that before.

315
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:32,920
I feel upset when we're on bad terms.

316
00:26:33,320 --> 00:26:34,480
Why?

317
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:36,240
What does it matter?

318
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:40,280
You do whatever you please, anyway.

319
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:42,040
Is there such a thing as "us?"

320
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:50,400
You're being unfair.

321
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:56,719
You're upsetting me, I feel especially

322
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:58,600
sad when you think and speak like this.

323
00:26:58,640 --> 00:27:00,000
So, it's my fault?

324
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:01,160
Huh?

325
00:27:01,840 --> 00:27:04,040
We've been through so much together and you

326
00:27:04,080 --> 00:27:06,200
still act as if you don't know me at all.

327
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:15,520
Then you should've acted accordingly.

328
00:27:17,320 --> 00:27:18,880
I was really worried about you.

329
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:27,880
I know.

330
00:27:29,080 --> 00:27:30,919
I acted without thinking.

331
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:32,520
I went there without a thought.

332
00:27:33,320 --> 00:27:34,760
I was in a panic.

333
00:27:38,440 --> 00:27:41,960
Now, I'm standing
here, before you, trying to explain myself.

334
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:44,240
I don't like this at all.

335
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:46,840
But you're right.

336
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:50,160
I would've been angry with me as well if I
were in your shoes.

337
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:53,200
I know you have a problem with Nezir,

338
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:57,520
but you, too, should understand me.

339
00:27:57,560 --> 00:27:59,480
Demet is really important to me.

340
00:28:04,520 --> 00:28:08,000
What did you mean upstairs, when you talked
of serious consequences?

341
00:28:14,920 --> 00:28:16,960
Do you know what this experience has taught
us?

342
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:20,120
Fatigue.

343
00:28:22,560 --> 00:28:23,840
You should go and rest.

344
00:28:28,080 --> 00:28:29,480
I was just warming up.

345
00:28:55,240 --> 00:28:56,559
Yes, Ms. Zahide?

346
00:28:56,560 --> 00:29:00,480
Hello, Mr. Ateş. It's
the last week for the art center in

347
00:29:00,520 --> 00:29:04,480
Italy, three other firms
are joining from Türkiye as well.

348
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:08,360
If we don't
make a move now, it may be too late for us.

349
00:29:08,400 --> 00:29:11,520
I can't deal with that
right now, let the other firms take it.

350
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,999
If you say so, okay.

351
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:16,320
Okay, thank you, Mr. Ateş.

352
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:48,520
What did Mr. Ateş say? Tell me.

353
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:49,520
What do you think?

354
00:29:49,521 --> 00:29:52,440
He said there's nothing we can do, let the
other firms take it.

355
00:29:53,440 --> 00:29:54,600
That's a shame.

356
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:56,000
What a shame.

357
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:59,360
We could've gone to Italy, maybe we'd have
had the chance.

358
00:30:04,800 --> 00:30:08,440
I should talk to Ms. Mercan
about it, try to get her involved.

359
00:30:09,280 --> 00:30:11,320
I don't think she would take this on right
now.

360
00:30:13,880 --> 00:30:14,960
She could, though.

361
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:18,960
I'll call her later.

362
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,080
Fine.

363
00:30:45,280 --> 00:30:46,320
Malik.

364
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:51,159
Malik, what are you doing here?

365
00:30:51,160 --> 00:30:52,400
Çiçek?

366
00:30:53,120 --> 00:30:54,600
What happened, have you been crying?

367
00:30:56,680 --> 00:30:57,760
What is it?

368
00:30:58,160 --> 00:30:59,720
Did you argue with your mom?

369
00:31:01,520 --> 00:31:05,320
I tried to convince her not to
send me away but she won't change her mind.

370
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:07,000
This won't do.

371
00:31:07,040 --> 00:31:08,400
It can't go on like this.

372
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:12,480
I don't want to be
away from you or my family, Malik.

373
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:16,160
I need to do something.

374
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:22,320
I can't let you get hurt because of me.

375
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:25,800
I can't just watch
you get seperated from your family.

376
00:31:27,120 --> 00:31:28,720
There's nothing you can do.

377
00:31:30,880 --> 00:31:33,600
The more I keep my silence
the more you struggle.

378
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:37,400
Mom won't see reason.

379
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:42,320
Your mom should see how much I love you,

380
00:31:42,360 --> 00:31:44,920
how serious I am about you, already.

381
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:48,360
How can we make her see?

382
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:51,120
You go inside for now,

383
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,280
try to relax.

384
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:54,200
Don't feel bad any longer.

385
00:31:54,640 --> 00:31:55,880
I'm going to handle it.

386
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:58,000
Trust me.

387
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:01,160
Just have trust in us.

388
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:02,440
Believe in us.

389
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:06,720
I will never, ever give up on you.

390
00:32:07,880 --> 00:32:09,240
Just keep believing.

391
00:32:11,840 --> 00:32:14,920
Both your mom and your
brother will understand, eventually.

392
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:16,640
Okay?

393
00:32:20,960 --> 00:32:22,240
I'll go now.

394
00:32:22,720 --> 00:32:23,760
See you.

395
00:33:24,080 --> 00:33:26,880
I'm so sorry, I'll leave right now.

396
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:28,600
There's no need.

397
00:33:35,040 --> 00:33:38,440
I can't get used to
knocking, that's why this keeps happening.

398
00:33:41,040 --> 00:33:42,040
Hold on.

399
00:33:43,320 --> 00:33:44,520
What is it?

400
00:33:45,520 --> 00:33:48,040
You put your sweater on
backwards, don't you see?

401
00:33:50,680 --> 00:33:51,880
Fix it at once.

402
00:33:52,640 --> 00:33:54,200
Or your luck will run backwards, too.

403
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:57,440
Whenever I put something
on backwards, everything goes wrong.

404
00:33:58,560 --> 00:34:01,120
Like nothing could ever have anything to do
with you.

405
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:03,040
It must be the clothes.

406
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:08,680
Believe or don't. I don't care.

407
00:34:18,480 --> 00:34:20,240
Did you put it on? I'm
going to turn around.

408
00:34:22,520 --> 00:34:23,560
Wait.

409
00:34:26,320 --> 00:34:27,520
What is it, now?

410
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:31,160
Let me fix this.

411
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:38,720
Our conversation got interrupted.

412
00:34:41,520 --> 00:34:43,160
Nothing was interrupted.

413
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:45,320
There's nothing else to talk about.

414
00:34:46,680 --> 00:34:49,200
You keep repeating the same things, anyway.

415
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:53,680
Fix it yourself.

416
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:55,679
There's no need.

417
00:34:55,680 --> 00:34:57,400
I like it messy, anyway.

418
00:34:58,240 --> 00:34:59,840
You should've said so.

419
00:35:00,520 --> 00:35:01,880
I would've if you'd asked.

420
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:06,360
Where are you going?

421
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,480
Do I have to report to you?

422
00:35:13,720 --> 00:35:15,080
Sorry, I forgot.

423
00:35:15,720 --> 00:35:18,400
I haven't reached interrogation status yet,
right.

424
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:24,079
I get interrogated
left and right and I have to report

425
00:35:24,080 --> 00:35:26,440
in detail but I can't do the same for some
reason.

426
00:35:27,720 --> 00:35:29,880
Do you realize that you're nagging me right
now?

427
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:33,119
Not at all.

428
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:35,000
I'm just speaking the truth.

429
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,800
Won't you tell me where you're going?

430
00:35:42,600 --> 00:35:44,480
I'll be in my office.

431
00:35:44,520 --> 00:35:45,760
I'm not going anywhere.

432
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:48,440
Okay? Are you satisfied?

433
00:35:49,520 --> 00:35:52,759
If there's anything
I could help with, I'm free. If you want...

434
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:53,800
There's no need.

435
00:35:57,120 --> 00:35:58,600
I'll handle it myself.

436
00:35:59,800 --> 00:36:01,200
I haven't forgotten what happened.

437
00:36:02,720 --> 00:36:04,880
It's my fault for offering to help.

438
00:36:12,080 --> 00:36:13,520
I can't believe him.

439
00:36:14,040 --> 00:36:15,400
He's still on the same subject.

440
00:36:16,680 --> 00:36:17,960
But it's my fault.

441
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:20,399
Why am I trying in vain to explain myself?

442
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:22,000
When has he understood?

443
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:24,080
What does he know of humanity?

444
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:28,760
He's the
one being unfair, yet, he's angry with me.

445
00:36:29,680 --> 00:36:31,440
But that's enough. What am I doing?

446
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:32,440
It's my fault.

447
00:36:32,480 --> 00:36:35,360
If he doesn't know me by now, it's on him.

448
00:36:35,400 --> 00:36:37,840
Why I constantly trying to explain myself?

449
00:36:38,840 --> 00:36:42,080
And he's so rude, too.
With his "Are you satisfied, that's

450
00:36:42,120 --> 00:36:45,480
the way I want it" and
it's my way or the highway attitude.

451
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:51,280
You're still here?

452
00:36:55,040 --> 00:36:57,840
You need some practice
on your Ateş impersonation.

453
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:05,160
I'll leave
you alone so you can keep impersonating me.

454
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:19,200
"I'll leave you alone
so you can keep impersonating me."

455
00:37:20,120 --> 00:37:21,160
Jerk.

456
00:37:21,520 --> 00:37:25,360
He's so crude. He's
such a bully. Nothing but a bully.

457
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:45,680
What happened?

458
00:37:46,040 --> 00:37:49,160
Haydar found out about your orphanage lie.

459
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:54,560
If he's still silent knowing this,

460
00:37:56,200 --> 00:37:58,400
he must have something else up his sleeve.

461
00:37:58,680 --> 00:37:59,760
Exactly.

462
00:38:00,440 --> 00:38:02,840
If he didn't, he
would've already played his hand.

463
00:38:04,520 --> 00:38:05,599
Keep your eye on him.

464
00:38:05,600 --> 00:38:06,720
I will, Ateş.

465
00:38:06,760 --> 00:38:08,120
Come on, Fatih, let's go.

466
00:38:17,800 --> 00:38:19,440
Are you doing research on me?

467
00:38:21,760 --> 00:38:22,800
Yes.

468
00:38:23,720 --> 00:38:25,719
I should've done so at the beginning.

469
00:38:25,720 --> 00:38:28,080
It was stupid of me to wait until now.

470
00:38:31,160 --> 00:38:32,720
It was really stupid.

471
00:38:34,800 --> 00:38:37,839
If it were me, I wouldn't have made a deal

472
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:40,880
with a stranger without doing my research.

473
00:38:42,360 --> 00:38:45,400
You left everything in my hands by signing
a

474
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:48,640
contract for money without
asking any questions.

475
00:38:49,600 --> 00:38:50,640
Don't worry.

476
00:38:51,960 --> 00:38:54,360
You'll have everything back when it's time.

477
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:57,840
Of course, if you abide by our deal.

478
00:39:00,760 --> 00:39:04,399
We didn't only make a business deal
with you, Ateş Karahan.

479
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:05,960
You married my daughter.

480
00:39:06,600 --> 00:39:09,000
Why did my research make you so uneasy?

481
00:39:12,680 --> 00:39:14,400
Research all you want,

482
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:17,320
but be careful.

483
00:39:18,040 --> 00:39:20,160
I wouldn't want you to
be crushed by what you find.

484
00:39:21,640 --> 00:39:24,279
You can find out, about my business

485
00:39:24,280 --> 00:39:27,000
and family, as much as I let you to.

486
00:39:38,680 --> 00:39:41,120
Someone must have told him about it.

487
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:45,560
I'll make sure whoever told him doesn't see
another day to run his mouth.

488
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:48,160
I'll make sure of it.

489
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:09,360
What are you thinking about so intently?

490
00:40:11,680 --> 00:40:14,040
The way Ateş acts worries me.

491
00:40:15,560 --> 00:40:17,640
He was so enraged, he looked like a madman.

492
00:40:17,680 --> 00:40:19,520
I'd never seen him like that.

493
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:24,879
We must be on the
right path if we managed to get him so mad.

494
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:30,480
The more he loses control, the easier
it will become to manipulate him.

495
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:34,560
It was like he'd lost
all his senses in a fit of jealousy.

496
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:36,960
He wants to believe Mercan is innocent.

497
00:40:38,040 --> 00:40:39,800
We can't let that happen, mom.

498
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:41,240
Of course we won't.

499
00:40:41,560 --> 00:40:43,400
I didn't come this far for nothing.

500
00:40:43,840 --> 00:40:45,760
I won't stop until they're all dead.

501
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:52,760
I'll destroy
Haydar's family just as he destroyed mine.

502
00:40:54,240 --> 00:40:55,360
Murat is dead.

503
00:40:56,760 --> 00:40:58,440
Now it's time for the rest of them.

504
00:41:00,040 --> 00:41:01,880
Ateş would never let that happen.

505
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:03,880
I know.

506
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:05,640
I'll wait patiently.

507
00:41:07,040 --> 00:41:09,760
Everything will change when he sees what

508
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:12,280
kind of person Haydar's daughter is.

509
00:41:13,400 --> 00:41:15,599
We need to keep Ateş under
control in the mean time.

510
00:41:15,600 --> 00:41:18,760
We need to get him to a point where
he won't even want to see her face.

511
00:41:21,400 --> 00:41:23,400
If we
can create some more problems one after the

512
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:25,440
other,
it'd be easier for him to forget about her.

513
00:41:26,640 --> 00:41:27,880
That's it, then.

514
00:41:27,920 --> 00:41:29,680
Let's do whatever it takes.

515
00:41:29,720 --> 00:41:31,880
While everything's already a mess.

516
00:41:33,200 --> 00:41:34,640
Of course we will.

517
00:41:35,640 --> 00:41:37,799
Or we'll lose everything we have.

518
00:41:37,800 --> 00:41:40,960
Mercan wouldn't let us get anywhere
near Ateş.

519
00:41:44,960 --> 00:41:47,920
That's why we won't leave
anything up to chance, this time.

520
00:41:48,760 --> 00:41:50,240
Do you have the pictures?

521
00:41:50,280 --> 00:41:51,360
Yes.

522
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:54,920
Okay.

523
00:42:20,840 --> 00:42:22,840
Oh no! My necklace.

524
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:26,880
It's broken.

525
00:42:27,880 --> 00:42:30,120
It's just a necklace, why are you so upset?

526
00:42:30,160 --> 00:42:31,360
Forget about it.

527
00:42:32,200 --> 00:42:33,600
Did it have sentimental value?

528
00:42:34,640 --> 00:42:36,640
No but I liked it.

529
00:43:41,600 --> 00:43:43,040
What happened, why are you up?

530
00:43:44,240 --> 00:43:45,400
Did you have a nightmare?

531
00:43:48,640 --> 00:43:50,560
What nightmare? I
couldn't even fall asleep.

532
00:43:56,280 --> 00:43:59,120
I was
worried about you, since you didn't return.

533
00:44:15,200 --> 00:44:18,360
"Even if it's on paper, she's your
wife, Ateş!"

534
00:44:19,520 --> 00:44:23,280
Her going to some strange man's house
to sleep around is unacceptable!

535
00:44:23,320 --> 00:44:26,680
Are you going to let them muddy our name?

536
00:44:30,200 --> 00:44:31,520
I'm busy with work.

537
00:44:38,400 --> 00:44:40,960
Did you practice your Ateş impersonation?

538
00:44:45,960 --> 00:44:47,880
I'm going to work, you go to sleep.

539
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:53,520
I'll sit
here and wait for you to finish your work.

540
00:44:55,200 --> 00:44:57,840
I'll get some work done alongside you.

541
00:44:59,040 --> 00:45:00,480
What are you working on?

542
00:45:07,840 --> 00:45:09,320
Should I bring us some coffee?

543
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:17,040
Or I could bring something to eat.

544
00:45:28,560 --> 00:45:30,080
I didn't do anything wrong.

545
00:45:31,000 --> 00:45:33,440
But you're making me feel guilty.

546
00:45:35,880 --> 00:45:38,000
You went to that man's
house without telling me.

547
00:45:39,560 --> 00:45:41,000
Okay, you're right.

548
00:45:41,880 --> 00:45:43,480
What more can I say?

549
00:45:45,400 --> 00:45:47,160
Why do you care so much?

550
00:45:48,200 --> 00:45:49,800
You still haven't answered.

551
00:45:51,760 --> 00:45:53,760
Why does everyone keep
asking the same question?

552
00:45:54,440 --> 00:45:55,800
Nothing's different.

553
00:45:56,640 --> 00:45:58,080
Who else asked?

554
00:46:01,120 --> 00:46:02,240
Forget about it.

555
00:46:08,160 --> 00:46:09,840
That's your only issue, I guess?

556
00:46:09,880 --> 00:46:11,000
Yes.

557
00:46:11,640 --> 00:46:13,200
What else could it be?

558
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:16,720
I'm going to work, you go and sleep.

559
00:46:18,240 --> 00:46:22,960
If you're not going to sleep, I'll sit here
until morning.

560
00:47:35,920 --> 00:47:37,280
My anger persists,

561
00:47:38,400 --> 00:47:40,160
but I can't stand to see you hurt.

562
00:48:43,760 --> 00:48:45,320
When did I fall asleep?

563
00:49:06,800 --> 00:49:08,280
Good morning, Ms. Mercan.

564
00:49:14,080 --> 00:49:15,440
Where is Ateş?

565
00:49:16,640 --> 00:49:18,600
I fell asleep here.

566
00:49:19,200 --> 00:49:20,839
Ateş forgot to take this.

567
00:49:20,840 --> 00:49:23,400
He's waiting for me
outside, we'll leave together in a minute.

568
00:49:25,680 --> 00:49:27,040
He's not waiting for me.

569
00:49:31,240 --> 00:49:33,520
But I said I'd come too.

570
00:50:29,840 --> 00:50:31,680
What, Nermin? What is it now?

571
00:50:33,080 --> 00:50:35,920
Haydar, I need money.

572
00:50:36,760 --> 00:50:38,480
Can you give me some money?

573
00:50:40,640 --> 00:50:41,960
Money for what?

574
00:50:42,680 --> 00:50:44,000
What do you mean money for what?

575
00:50:44,480 --> 00:50:45,880
I just need money.

576
00:50:46,880 --> 00:50:48,520
Are you serious right now?

577
00:50:51,040 --> 00:50:55,720
Look, Haydar. I need money
to win the chairmanship.

578
00:50:56,560 --> 00:50:58,920
You're supposed to buy
some gifts, you know.

579
00:51:00,400 --> 00:51:04,280
I don't know if you realize this but we're
still in a bad place.

580
00:51:07,440 --> 00:51:09,160
Nezir barely pays us.

581
00:51:09,200 --> 00:51:11,200
Don't
draw attention, they'll think we're broke.

582
00:51:13,040 --> 00:51:15,321
You get no respect in
this world if you don't have money.

583
00:51:16,560 --> 00:51:20,040
Don't get me involved with
these people for your stupid chairmanship.

584
00:51:20,800 --> 00:51:22,120
What nonsense.

585
00:51:49,720 --> 00:51:50,960
Here you go.

586
00:51:51,760 --> 00:51:52,720
Thanks, man.

587
00:51:52,721 --> 00:51:53,880
Enjoy.

588
00:51:54,320 --> 00:51:55,360
Burak.

589
00:51:58,400 --> 00:52:00,760
I know you're avoiding
me because of my brother.

590
00:52:04,000 --> 00:52:06,440
You don't have to avoid me, Burak.

591
00:52:07,160 --> 00:52:09,240
Nezir doesn't have a say in my decisions.

592
00:52:09,760 --> 00:52:11,439
I made this very clear to him, as well.

593
00:52:11,440 --> 00:52:12,800
I'm not a kid.

594
00:52:13,200 --> 00:52:15,360
I decide who I want to see.

595
00:52:17,280 --> 00:52:19,720
I'm so sorry he bullied you.

596
00:52:19,760 --> 00:52:20,880
Really.

597
00:52:22,040 --> 00:52:23,800
I'm apologizing to you on his behalf.

598
00:52:24,080 --> 00:52:25,199
Demet.

599
00:52:25,200 --> 00:52:27,080
You don't need to apologize.

600
00:52:27,120 --> 00:52:29,960
He's trying to protect
his sister in his own way.

601
00:52:30,560 --> 00:52:34,760
Listen, Demet. Family is a person's weakest
spot.

602
00:52:35,040 --> 00:52:37,160
I've never had that kind of bond
in my life.

603
00:52:37,760 --> 00:52:40,800
That's why I wouldn't
want to cast a shadow on your family bonds.

604
00:52:42,040 --> 00:52:44,160
It's best if we stayed
away from one another.

605
00:53:12,760 --> 00:53:14,160
Sorry to disturb you.

606
00:53:14,440 --> 00:53:15,680
You're not, Berat. Come.

607
00:53:16,880 --> 00:53:19,800
Mr. Haydar, I can't thank you enough.

608
00:53:21,280 --> 00:53:25,560
Thank you so much, I don't
know how to repay this kindness.

609
00:53:26,240 --> 00:53:28,359
I'll never forget about
it, Mr. Haydar. Thank you

610
00:53:28,360 --> 00:53:30,400
so much. I'll do everything in my power for
you,

611
00:53:30,440 --> 00:53:31,840
I promise.

612
00:53:33,760 --> 00:53:34,960
That's good.

613
00:53:36,640 --> 00:53:41,520
First thing I want you to do is get
close to Cemal and keep your eye on him.

614
00:53:47,520 --> 00:53:49,519
But Mr. Cemal is part of the

615
00:53:49,520 --> 00:53:51,560
Karahan family, Mr. Haydar.

616
00:53:53,920 --> 00:53:58,280
Our living under the same roof doesn't mean
we're on the same side, son.

617
00:54:02,520 --> 00:54:05,560
Don't you ever forget
who your loyalty is to.

618
00:54:07,240 --> 00:54:09,360
Of course. Of course, sir. Don't worry.

619
00:54:11,520 --> 00:54:13,600
I have big plans for you.

620
00:54:13,640 --> 00:54:15,600
I'm going to make you my right arm man.

621
00:54:18,160 --> 00:54:19,400
What is he saying?

622
00:54:22,640 --> 00:54:23,880
Don't forget what I told you.

623
00:54:27,800 --> 00:54:29,800
Keep Cemal under your watch at all times.

624
00:54:37,680 --> 00:54:40,640
Ms. Binnaz, make me a
coffee. I'll be in the living room.

625
00:55:04,320 --> 00:55:07,000
Berat, what are you doing with Mr. Haydar?

626
00:55:08,640 --> 00:55:13,600
Nothing, mom. I was just asking him how he
was.

627
00:55:14,200 --> 00:55:16,080
You stay away from him, Berat.

628
00:55:16,600 --> 00:55:18,720
You're not in that man's league.

629
00:55:18,760 --> 00:55:20,160
He's your boss, after all.

630
00:55:20,200 --> 00:55:24,080
There needs to be a boundary between you,
and you don't cross it. Do you hear me?

631
00:55:25,760 --> 00:55:29,800
Of course, mom. I'm well
aware of that. Don't worry, it was nothing.

632
00:55:31,200 --> 00:55:32,360
Good.

633
00:55:53,280 --> 00:55:56,960
The economy journal wants to interview you.

634
00:56:13,640 --> 00:56:16,960
What happened with Mercan? Did you bury the
hatchet?

635
00:56:19,240 --> 00:56:20,360
I don't know.

636
00:56:23,960 --> 00:56:26,600
She got really upset this morning
because you didn't wait for her.

637
00:56:29,760 --> 00:56:31,360
You trust Mercan, I know.

638
00:56:34,560 --> 00:56:36,120
She's not the one I don't trust.

639
00:56:41,240 --> 00:56:43,640
I'm angry that she doesn't see that.

640
00:56:57,640 --> 00:56:59,120
Excuse me.

641
00:57:07,200 --> 00:57:09,120
Why didn't you wait for me?

642
00:57:10,760 --> 00:57:12,240
Do I have to wait for you?

643
00:57:24,520 --> 00:57:26,280
Yesterday was a big misunderstanding.

644
00:57:27,240 --> 00:57:29,560
None of that would've
happened if you listened first.

645
00:57:37,840 --> 00:57:40,320
Moving in anger never solves anything.

646
00:57:44,440 --> 00:57:46,000
If only we remained calm.

647
00:57:48,160 --> 00:57:49,960
What are you trying to tell me?

648
00:57:51,200 --> 00:57:53,200
I'm just saying you jump
to the worst conclusion

649
00:57:53,240 --> 00:57:55,000
because you don't know Mercan well enough.

650
00:57:59,080 --> 00:58:01,280
If I were in your place, I'd never have

651
00:58:01,320 --> 00:58:03,360
made the mistake of not trusting her.

652
00:58:07,320 --> 00:58:10,880
You shouldn't try
to figure out what I'm thinking.

653
00:58:14,360 --> 00:58:16,920
Nezir. Please, go.

654
00:58:23,520 --> 00:58:25,920
I'm only trying to help Mercan.

655
00:58:26,440 --> 00:58:27,840
So she's not in a tough spot.

656
00:58:30,720 --> 00:58:32,920
I would be thanking me if I were you.

657
00:58:52,760 --> 00:58:53,960
Why are you here?

658
00:58:54,680 --> 00:58:56,520
Why do you keep giving
me the cold shoulder?

659
00:58:56,560 --> 00:59:00,240
I've been trying to explain myself
to you since yesterday.

660
00:59:00,800 --> 00:59:02,440
But I see now that it was in vain.

661
00:59:03,080 --> 00:59:05,040
I'm sick and tired of this.

662
00:59:06,400 --> 00:59:08,880
Whatever the consequence is let me have it,
so this can end.

663
00:59:08,920 --> 00:59:10,400
I'm busy.

664
00:59:10,440 --> 00:59:11,840
Get out.

665
00:59:55,520 --> 00:59:57,960
Ms. Binnaz, can we talk?

666
01:00:03,960 --> 01:00:06,040
I love your daughter very much.

667
01:00:07,760 --> 01:00:12,320
It's such a love that
it surpasses me or anything else I love.

668
01:00:15,360 --> 01:00:19,240
I would never upset or hurt her.

669
01:00:25,840 --> 01:00:28,440
Your
telling me to stay away from your daughter

670
01:00:28,480 --> 01:00:30,640
is a punishment worse than death for me.

671
01:00:33,080 --> 01:00:35,279
I understand your concern as a mother,

672
01:00:35,280 --> 01:00:37,640
you naturally want to
protect your daughter.

673
01:00:39,120 --> 01:00:44,760
But I just want you to
know, I'd also protect Çiçek with my life.

674
01:00:52,440 --> 01:00:55,880
I'd give everything
up to make her happy, even myself.

675
01:00:58,760 --> 01:01:00,600
You just trust us.

676
01:01:02,840 --> 01:01:04,000
Believe us.

677
01:01:04,040 --> 01:01:07,440
Let me protect
and provide for Çiçek as long as I'm alive.

678
01:01:08,640 --> 01:01:09,920
Please.

679
01:01:11,560 --> 01:01:14,440
You don't need to
prove yourself to me, I know you.

680
01:01:15,200 --> 01:01:18,440
You're a good,
honest and honorable man, I have to admit.

681
01:01:18,480 --> 01:01:22,280
You were there
for us on a rainy day, thank you for that.

682
01:01:25,400 --> 01:01:29,480
My problem is not with you, your character
or the work that you do.

683
01:01:29,520 --> 01:01:32,320
My problem is with my daughter.

684
01:01:39,280 --> 01:01:40,720
You're not from here.

685
01:01:40,760 --> 01:01:43,640
You'll eventually go back to your country.

686
01:01:43,680 --> 01:01:44,760
You will.

687
01:01:45,800 --> 01:01:48,800
But I can't send my daughter to a
foreign country, do you hear me?

688
01:01:50,280 --> 01:01:52,439
I suffered a lot in foreign lands.

689
01:01:52,440 --> 01:01:56,200
I can't put my own child
through the same pain.

690
01:01:56,240 --> 01:01:57,680
Do you understand?

691
01:01:58,800 --> 01:02:01,080
Ms. Binnaz, I'll stay here if I have to.

692
01:02:01,800 --> 01:02:03,640
I'll stay wherever Çiçek is.

693
01:02:11,480 --> 01:02:13,280
Just give us a chance.

694
01:02:13,320 --> 01:02:14,920
Have some trust.

695
01:02:16,600 --> 01:02:17,640
Please.

696
01:02:19,640 --> 01:02:21,800
I won't move
a step away, I'll stay here, I'll

697
01:02:21,840 --> 01:02:24,120
stay by Çiçek, wherever Çiçek is I'll stay
there.

698
01:02:25,840 --> 01:02:28,280
Give us a chance, please.

699
01:02:30,080 --> 01:02:31,520
I'll stay wherever she is.

700
01:02:33,600 --> 01:02:35,720
Give us a chance, please.

701
01:02:56,400 --> 01:02:58,720
What are your thoughts on this, Ms. Aslı?

702
01:03:08,760 --> 01:03:10,920
What are your thoughts, Mr. Ateş?

703
01:03:17,680 --> 01:03:19,080
It could work.

704
01:03:27,200 --> 01:03:30,200
Nezir. Please, go.

705
01:03:35,400 --> 01:03:37,239
I didn't do anything wrong.

706
01:03:37,240 --> 01:03:40,320
But you're making me feel guilty.

707
01:03:44,640 --> 01:03:47,680
Alright, everyone. This
concludes our meeting.

708
01:03:47,720 --> 01:03:49,519
Everyone get back to work.

709
01:03:49,520 --> 01:03:51,320
Ms. Zahide, Aslı.

710
01:04:14,880 --> 01:04:17,000
I know where your mind's at very well.

711
01:04:20,760 --> 01:04:23,120
I think you should resolve
this issue before it's too late.

712
01:04:25,120 --> 01:04:27,720
I told Mercan it would have consequences.

713
01:04:29,280 --> 01:04:32,080
You obviously have something on your mind.

714
01:04:35,400 --> 01:04:37,600
I'm thinking about firing her.

715
01:04:41,360 --> 01:04:42,760
That's a big consequence.

716
01:04:44,880 --> 01:04:46,440
Work is everything to her.

717
01:04:47,960 --> 01:04:51,440
Ateş, I think you should reconsider.

718
01:05:55,760 --> 01:05:57,160
We need to talk.

719
01:05:59,000 --> 01:06:00,199
Should we go inside?

720
01:06:00,200 --> 01:06:01,720
There's no need.

721
01:06:06,440 --> 01:06:08,320
You asked about the consequences.

722
01:06:14,440 --> 01:06:17,080
I can't believe it, that's crazy.

723
01:06:22,840 --> 01:06:24,080
What's going on?

724
01:06:24,200 --> 01:06:26,080
Did something happen?

725
01:06:36,240 --> 01:06:37,440
I don't know.

726
01:06:43,040 --> 01:06:44,440
Ateş, take a look at this.

727
01:07:09,640 --> 01:07:11,600
They're probably looking at this, too.

728
01:07:19,880 --> 01:07:20,920
What is it?

729
01:07:36,560 --> 01:07:38,120
Is there something wrong?

730
01:08:03,600 --> 01:08:05,960
So, this is
the consequence you talked about.

731
01:09:32,880 --> 01:09:35,600
No, no. This can't be.

732
01:09:36,680 --> 01:09:38,040
This can't be.

733
01:10:18,280 --> 01:10:20,040
This is the consequence you talked about?

734
01:10:20,400 --> 01:10:21,160
Huh?

735
01:10:21,161 --> 01:10:22,360
What are you saying?

736
01:10:47,160 --> 01:10:49,080
You didn't do this, you wouldn't, right?

737
01:10:50,840 --> 01:10:52,160
Tell me!

738
01:10:53,160 --> 01:10:54,439
Speak.

739
01:10:54,440 --> 01:10:56,199
You wouldn't do this.

740
01:10:56,200 --> 01:10:58,240
Is that really what you think?

741
01:11:01,280 --> 01:11:03,840
I don't know what to think anymore!

742
01:11:05,480 --> 01:11:07,240
Who would do this, for what?

743
01:11:10,960 --> 01:11:14,120
Why aren't
you saying anything? Say something, speak!

744
01:11:16,880 --> 01:11:18,720
Why are you so quiet?

745
01:11:19,120 --> 01:11:21,320
I don't get it, why are
you not saying anything?

746
01:11:22,280 --> 01:11:24,840
I don't have to tell you anything.

747
01:11:27,400 --> 01:11:28,920
You don't have to, is that so?

748
01:11:30,680 --> 01:11:32,600
This is my integrity, we're talking about.

749
01:11:33,120 --> 01:11:34,440
My honor!

750
01:11:35,640 --> 01:11:37,440
They did this to your wife.

751
01:11:49,880 --> 01:11:53,000
You keep telling me I'm a Karahan, right?

752
01:11:53,480 --> 01:11:55,160
They did this to a Karahan!

753
01:12:01,960 --> 01:12:03,960
I was very wrong about you.

754
01:12:05,440 --> 01:12:07,360
I thought you were different.

755
01:12:08,960 --> 01:12:11,720
I thought you weren't like Ms. Müzeyyen and
Aslı.

756
01:12:14,160 --> 01:12:18,040
But you are on the dark
side, just like they are.

757
01:13:44,600 --> 01:13:46,960
How can you hold her hand, Ateş?

758
01:13:50,040 --> 01:13:53,959
I see everyone's having a blast,
you all look like you're enjoying a movie.

759
01:13:53,960 --> 01:13:55,360
Are you comfortable?

760
01:13:55,840 --> 01:13:57,399
Everyone, get back to work.

761
01:13:57,400 --> 01:14:00,000
I must be the only
one who has any work to do in this company.

762
01:14:22,960 --> 01:14:24,400
You look thoughtful, honey.

763
01:14:26,600 --> 01:14:29,320
I have a million problems to work through.

764
01:14:29,680 --> 01:14:30,880
Of course, I'm thoughtful.

765
01:14:37,840 --> 01:14:40,400
Haydar, what are you doing? Keep that away
from me.

766
01:14:41,320 --> 01:14:43,079
It's not your first time seeing one.

767
01:14:43,080 --> 01:14:45,280
Don't you know I always have one on me?

768
01:14:45,960 --> 01:14:47,720
What will you do with that gun?

769
01:14:50,960 --> 01:14:52,280
Today is an important day.

770
01:14:52,960 --> 01:14:55,240
I'm going after one of the big ones.

771
01:14:56,120 --> 01:14:59,400
I'll find out the most sensitive secrets of
Ateş.

772
01:15:01,800 --> 01:15:03,000
Honey.

773
01:15:03,280 --> 01:15:05,319
Please, be careful.

774
01:15:05,320 --> 01:15:07,960
I get terrified that something will happen
to you.

775
01:15:10,160 --> 01:15:12,441
If you're going to ask
for money again, I don't have any,

776
01:15:12,480 --> 01:15:13,560
Nermin.

777
01:15:21,440 --> 01:15:23,920
I know where I can get that money.

778
01:15:47,000 --> 01:15:48,280
Mom.

779
01:15:50,000 --> 01:15:52,760
Won't you say something
about Malik's speech?

780
01:15:53,120 --> 01:15:54,200
What do you think?

781
01:15:56,080 --> 01:15:57,600
Give me the tomato paste.

782
01:16:04,120 --> 01:16:05,520
Mom, are you okay?

783
01:16:11,480 --> 01:16:15,320
Fill that kettle over there, I'm
going to need hot water for the food.

784
01:16:35,040 --> 01:16:36,080
Mom.

785
01:16:36,680 --> 01:16:38,680
Malik said he would stay.

786
01:16:38,720 --> 01:16:42,000
What do you think about
that? Why are not saying anything?

787
01:16:42,440 --> 01:16:45,600
Bring those turnips as well, we'll put some
into the salad.

788
01:16:54,800 --> 01:16:59,320
Go to the other kitchen and
get some rice, we don't have any left here.

789
01:16:59,360 --> 01:17:01,480
Okay, mom.

790
01:17:02,440 --> 01:17:04,040
Don't talk to me.

791
01:17:04,080 --> 01:17:05,080
Fine.

792
01:17:08,080 --> 01:17:10,160
This is not right, what you're doing.

793
01:17:13,160 --> 01:17:16,440
I didn't do
anything wrong. Malik didn't either.

794
01:17:17,200 --> 01:17:18,960
We love each other, that's all.

795
01:17:22,240 --> 01:17:25,880
Your treating him like this when
he has done nothing wrong makes me so sad.

796
01:17:29,120 --> 01:17:30,520
But okay, fine.

797
01:17:31,240 --> 01:17:32,480
It's fine.

798
01:17:36,080 --> 01:17:38,080
God give me patience!

799
01:18:10,400 --> 01:18:14,320
But you are on the dark
side, just like they are.

800
01:18:20,640 --> 01:18:22,600
Will you not say anything?

801
01:18:26,760 --> 01:18:28,080
What do you expect me to say?

802
01:18:32,520 --> 01:18:34,400
Will anything I say make a difference?

803
01:18:35,120 --> 01:18:36,399
Maybe it will.

804
01:18:36,400 --> 01:18:37,960
You should at least try.

805
01:18:39,480 --> 01:18:41,560
Will your embarrassment go away?

806
01:18:42,680 --> 01:18:44,160
Will your anger dwindle?

807
01:18:45,760 --> 01:18:46,800
No.

808
01:18:47,880 --> 01:18:49,440
But at least, I'll know.

809
01:18:50,600 --> 01:18:52,040
Know what?

810
01:18:52,800 --> 01:18:54,400
Who did this.

811
01:18:55,760 --> 01:18:57,440
Someone took pictures of me there.

812
01:18:58,520 --> 01:19:02,440
In a way that
looked like we were up close and personal.

813
01:19:09,200 --> 01:19:11,360
Someone must have followed me.

814
01:19:16,160 --> 01:19:18,960
And whoever they are,
they obviously don't have pure intentions.

815
01:19:20,280 --> 01:19:22,240
Am I not right in wanting to find out?

816
01:19:28,080 --> 01:19:31,760
Now that I think about it, How did you know
I was there?

817
01:19:35,880 --> 01:19:37,200
Who told you?

818
01:19:39,280 --> 01:19:41,160
Or was it you who had me followed?

819
01:19:50,680 --> 01:19:52,280
You didn't do that, did you?

820
01:19:53,920 --> 01:19:56,760
You won't get to
hear a word from me on this topic.

821
01:19:58,280 --> 01:20:02,760
Whatever you
want to believe becomes the truth.

822
01:20:04,000 --> 01:20:07,400
Constantly trying
to explain yourself to someone and

823
01:20:07,440 --> 01:20:10,800
their not
believing you feels horrible, does it not?

824
01:20:11,560 --> 01:20:13,160
You understand how I feel now.

825
01:20:57,680 --> 01:20:58,800
Yes, brother?

826
01:20:59,800 --> 01:21:01,840
Cemal, talk to the lawyer.

827
01:21:01,880 --> 01:21:05,959
Have him get a broadcast
ban on Mercan's pictures.

828
01:21:05,960 --> 01:21:08,440
Have him destroy all of them, if possible.

829
01:21:09,040 --> 01:21:11,760
Okay, I'm on it. Don't you worry.

830
01:21:40,000 --> 01:21:43,080
Come on, Zehra. Show up already, come on.

831
01:21:43,960 --> 01:21:45,440
Someone will see me waiting.

832
01:21:57,600 --> 01:21:59,480
My queen. Let me help you.

833
01:22:00,920 --> 01:22:02,040
Welcome.

834
01:22:02,480 --> 01:22:03,560
How are you?

835
01:22:03,600 --> 01:22:04,640
Fine.

836
01:22:06,400 --> 01:22:10,080
Where have you been, Zehra? I've missed you
so much.

837
01:22:10,720 --> 01:22:12,160
I just managed to get free.

838
01:22:12,800 --> 01:22:14,879
It's not like you're coming from some

839
01:22:14,880 --> 01:22:17,160
foreign land, it was just two steps away.

840
01:22:17,200 --> 01:22:19,160
I'm not in the mood to joke around, Berat.

841
01:22:22,800 --> 01:22:25,720
Did something happen? Why are you so upset,
Zehra?

842
01:22:26,240 --> 01:22:27,840
You still haven't figured it out?

843
01:22:28,720 --> 01:22:29,799
What?

844
01:22:29,800 --> 01:22:31,400
You don't know why I'm upset?

845
01:22:31,440 --> 01:22:32,560
No.

846
01:22:34,960 --> 01:22:37,400
You talk all sweetly, compliment me

847
01:22:37,440 --> 01:22:39,760
all the time but it's all a show.

848
01:22:39,800 --> 01:22:41,440
You're all talk and no walk.

849
01:22:42,120 --> 01:22:45,480
You can't be half the
man Malik is, shame on you!

850
01:22:46,920 --> 01:22:50,200
You've completely ruined my mood
by speaking his name.

851
01:22:50,600 --> 01:22:52,440
I'm only telling the truth.

852
01:22:53,240 --> 01:22:55,600
Look at how he fights for his love.

853
01:22:55,640 --> 01:22:58,160
He stood up even to you for his love.

854
01:23:00,040 --> 01:23:03,080
Let me tell you this,
there's no way that'll happen.

855
01:23:03,720 --> 01:23:05,720
You'll see how he'll make it work.

856
01:23:06,480 --> 01:23:09,280
You'll see how he'll convince both you and

857
01:23:09,320 --> 01:23:12,040
your mother by whatever means necessary.

858
01:23:12,800 --> 01:23:15,480
He'll put that ring on Çiçek's finger.

859
01:23:17,520 --> 01:23:22,159
A man who's gone behind my back, can't even
step foot into our house let

860
01:23:22,160 --> 01:23:24,839
alone put a ring on my sister's finger.

861
01:23:24,840 --> 01:23:27,040
I'm calling it now, I'm sure of it.

862
01:23:28,600 --> 01:23:30,119
Malik will marry Çiçek.

863
01:23:30,120 --> 01:23:31,999
Do you know why, Berat?

864
01:23:32,000 --> 01:23:34,120
Because he's not a coward like you.

865
01:23:34,920 --> 01:23:36,320
He doesn't run from marriage.

866
01:23:36,800 --> 01:23:39,680
I didn't hear anything
about marriage come out of your mouth once.

867
01:23:42,120 --> 01:23:45,560
Zehra, it hasn't even been that long.

868
01:23:48,640 --> 01:23:51,679
Hearing the
word "marriage" all of a sudden,

869
01:23:51,680 --> 01:23:52,960
I'm taken aback a little.

870
01:23:53,280 --> 01:23:54,600
I get it, Berat.

871
01:23:55,720 --> 01:23:57,320
You're not serious about me.

872
01:23:59,080 --> 01:24:01,640
I see, you're just playing with me.

873
01:24:02,040 --> 01:24:04,760
But look,
do I look like the type to be played? Huh?

874
01:24:06,640 --> 01:24:07,720
My queen.

875
01:24:09,720 --> 01:24:10,720
I mean...

876
01:24:11,040 --> 01:24:12,079
What?

877
01:24:12,080 --> 01:24:13,680
Please, don't be like this.

878
01:24:14,720 --> 01:24:18,920
I mean, I enjoy the game too, but...

879
01:24:18,960 --> 01:24:20,079
What?

880
01:24:20,080 --> 01:24:23,919
No, no! I didn't mean
it like that. You misunderstood.

881
01:24:23,920 --> 01:24:29,120
When I say game I mean I enjoy the flirting
and the bickering, you misunderstood me.

882
01:24:29,840 --> 01:24:32,040
Don't look at me like you don't believe me.

883
01:24:34,160 --> 01:24:35,280
Suit yourself, Berat.

884
01:24:35,320 --> 01:24:38,680
If you're not serious about me, let's stop
seeing each other.

885
01:24:39,840 --> 01:24:41,000
That would be best.

886
01:24:42,360 --> 01:24:44,800
I'll be hurt but it'll pass.

887
01:24:46,400 --> 01:24:49,320
Everything is temporary in life,
the pain of love will pass just as well.

888
01:24:50,320 --> 01:24:51,760
I'll see it through if it's my fate.

889
01:24:53,000 --> 01:24:55,880
But I won't let anyone make me hang my head
in shame, do you hear me?

890
01:24:55,920 --> 01:24:57,240
It's no problem.

891
01:25:08,640 --> 01:25:10,440
What did I do wrong, now?

892
01:25:54,160 --> 01:25:55,639
So long.

893
01:25:55,640 --> 01:25:56,760
Goodbye.

894
01:26:12,840 --> 01:26:16,440
You posted the pictures online, didn't you?

895
01:26:19,000 --> 01:26:20,480
Yes, I did.

896
01:26:20,840 --> 01:26:22,240
And I'm glad I did.

897
01:26:22,280 --> 01:26:23,680
I didn't hesitate at all.

898
01:26:25,120 --> 01:26:27,080
How could you cause such an embarrassment?

899
01:26:29,000 --> 01:26:32,080
I'm not the one who caused
this embarrassment but that little

900
01:26:32,120 --> 01:26:35,199
snake who keeps forgetting
she's married and playing around.

901
01:26:35,200 --> 01:26:36,720
Mom!

902
01:26:38,200 --> 01:26:40,360
How
can you call into question a woman's honor?

903
01:26:41,320 --> 01:26:42,520
You're a woman, too!

904
01:26:43,520 --> 01:26:44,760
How could you do this?

905
01:26:46,320 --> 01:26:50,440
I only made everyone find
out what we already knew.

906
01:26:52,200 --> 01:26:54,720
I only announced what was already obvious.

907
01:26:58,640 --> 01:26:59,720
That's what you did, huh?

908
01:27:00,840 --> 01:27:03,360
Do you realize the position you put me in,
then?

909
01:27:04,440 --> 01:27:06,400
People will say my wife is cheating on me.

910
01:27:07,000 --> 01:27:08,280
What about me?

911
01:27:09,880 --> 01:27:12,120
Mercan carries the Karahan name.

912
01:27:12,880 --> 01:27:16,720
It's not just her who's been
put to shame, but you and I and all of us!

913
01:27:16,960 --> 01:27:18,840
How can you not consider this?

914
01:27:19,280 --> 01:27:20,640
How could you do such a thing?

915
01:27:21,720 --> 01:27:23,879
Why do you keep walking over me?

916
01:27:23,880 --> 01:27:25,120
Why won't you stop?

917
01:27:26,360 --> 01:27:27,479
I can't stop.

918
01:27:27,480 --> 01:27:28,880
I won't stop.

919
01:27:31,320 --> 01:27:32,920
This is unforgivable.

920
01:27:34,440 --> 01:27:36,080
I have infinite respect for you.

921
01:27:36,840 --> 01:27:38,120
You practically raised me.

922
01:27:39,200 --> 01:27:41,120
But I won't let you do
this, there's a line.

923
01:27:44,840 --> 01:27:46,800
How many more times do I have to tell you?

924
01:27:47,720 --> 01:27:50,280
You'll first have
to deal with me if you try to hurt Mercan.

925
01:27:51,280 --> 01:27:53,360
Mercan has immunity, okay?

926
01:27:54,280 --> 01:27:55,680
Learn this, already.

927
01:27:57,680 --> 01:28:02,240
If you think I'll go easy
on you, you're gravely mistaken.

928
01:28:03,560 --> 01:28:06,640
That girl may be out of your revenge plan,
Ateş.

929
01:28:07,160 --> 01:28:10,280
But she's still Haydar
Yıldırım's daughter to me.

930
01:28:11,000 --> 01:28:14,880
She's only getting what she deserves
from my anger and she'll keep getting it.

931
01:29:34,120 --> 01:29:37,199
I can't believe it, that's crazy,
look at this.

932
01:29:37,200 --> 01:29:39,320
That's unbelievable, there's no way.

933
01:29:51,680 --> 01:29:53,600
My god, please help me.

934
01:29:54,840 --> 01:29:57,479
Please give me strength
to deal with this embarrassment.

935
01:29:57,480 --> 01:29:58,840
Please.

936
01:30:09,040 --> 01:30:10,160
Mercan?

937
01:30:10,200 --> 01:30:11,440
Dear.

938
01:30:12,680 --> 01:30:14,480
Why are you crying?

939
01:30:15,760 --> 01:30:17,160
Don't you fall apart.

940
01:30:18,800 --> 01:30:21,199
Didn't you see
the article? They wrote horrendous things.

941
01:30:21,200 --> 01:30:22,520
I saw it.

942
01:30:22,880 --> 01:30:24,400
Let them write whatever they want.

943
01:30:24,920 --> 01:30:26,560
People will forget about it in 2 days.

944
01:30:27,040 --> 01:30:28,200
Don't you mind it.

945
01:30:28,240 --> 01:30:29,279
How can I not?

946
01:30:29,280 --> 01:30:30,400
Just don't.

947
01:30:31,800 --> 01:30:34,200
It must've been that witch Müzeyyen.

948
01:30:35,120 --> 01:30:37,800
They're trying to ruin
our family's reputation.

949
01:30:39,360 --> 01:30:41,080
But I'll take revenge on them.

950
01:30:41,880 --> 01:30:44,879
Once I take
the chairmanship position from her, she'll

951
01:30:44,880 --> 01:30:47,600
regret ever touching Nermin
Yıldırım's daughter.

952
01:30:48,960 --> 01:30:50,400
Don't you feel sad, okay?

953
01:30:53,800 --> 01:30:55,120
My beautiful girl.

954
01:31:15,240 --> 01:31:16,440
Demet?

955
01:31:16,480 --> 01:31:17,800
Mercan.

956
01:31:18,560 --> 01:31:21,000
How are you, dear?
I've been worried sick about you.

957
01:31:22,520 --> 01:31:24,320
I'm not okay, Demet.

958
01:31:25,000 --> 01:31:26,280
My dear friend.

959
01:31:26,600 --> 01:31:28,440
I'll be right there.

960
01:31:37,360 --> 01:31:40,000
He
Protected Mercan with all his might, again.

961
01:31:40,560 --> 01:31:42,760
But I didn't back down, either.

962
01:31:42,800 --> 01:31:44,119
You did well, mom.

963
01:31:44,120 --> 01:31:45,480
Of course, I did well.

964
01:31:46,000 --> 01:31:48,640
Someone had to remind Ateş why he ever

965
01:31:48,680 --> 01:31:51,480
came to this house and who that girl is.

966
01:31:51,520 --> 01:31:54,640
I wish you'd seen
the state of Mercan at the company.

967
01:31:57,880 --> 01:32:01,360
She looked like
she wanted the ground to swallow her whole.

968
01:32:02,800 --> 01:32:05,040
She had to run out of there.

969
01:32:05,640 --> 01:32:08,080
I wish her the worst,
the murderer's daughter.

970
01:32:09,080 --> 01:32:11,200
I found a photgrapher by the way.

971
01:32:11,600 --> 01:32:14,160
He said we
can have the family shoot for the

972
01:32:14,200 --> 01:32:16,719
organization's chairmanship this afternoon.

973
01:32:16,720 --> 01:32:18,120
That's great.

974
01:32:18,960 --> 01:32:22,440
Let Ateş and
Cemal know, so they can get ready by then.

975
01:32:23,000 --> 01:32:24,720
I'll tell the kitchen staff to prepare

976
01:32:24,760 --> 01:32:26,279
some complimentary food and drinks.

977
01:32:26,280 --> 01:32:28,360
They should clean the house, too.

978
01:32:30,600 --> 01:32:34,120
This will be the best family
photo we've ever had taken until now.

979
01:32:34,880 --> 01:32:37,760
Everyone will see our power and nobility.

980
01:32:39,400 --> 01:32:40,400
Mom?

981
01:32:40,440 --> 01:32:41,840
What will you wear?

982
01:32:42,640 --> 01:32:45,120
Oh, I completely forgot about that.

983
01:32:47,200 --> 01:32:50,960
Come on, let's go shopping.
We'll get ourselves something nice.

984
01:32:51,920 --> 01:32:53,680
That's a really good idea.

985
01:32:54,760 --> 01:32:58,680
I won't have to go through my entire closet
trying to figure out what to wear.

986
01:32:59,800 --> 01:33:01,040
Come on, then.

987
01:33:02,120 --> 01:33:02,920
Now?

988
01:33:02,921 --> 01:33:04,080
Yes, now.

989
01:33:05,680 --> 01:33:06,760
Let's go.

990
01:33:08,640 --> 01:33:09,640
You funny girl.

991
01:34:01,360 --> 01:34:02,400
Are you okay?

992
01:34:14,160 --> 01:34:15,520
I asked if you're okay.

993
01:34:18,000 --> 01:34:19,040
I'm not.

994
01:34:20,400 --> 01:34:22,040
How can I be okay?

995
01:34:38,160 --> 01:34:39,400
Don't.

996
01:34:44,160 --> 01:34:46,560
You can't make me cry
and then try to console me.

997
01:34:49,200 --> 01:34:50,560
I don't want you to cry.

998
01:34:51,560 --> 01:34:53,320
Then, why hurt me?

999
01:34:56,880 --> 01:34:58,640
What do you want from me?

1000
01:34:58,680 --> 01:35:01,240
I've tried to tell you multiple times.

1001
01:35:01,720 --> 01:35:03,080
But nothing works.

1002
01:35:04,680 --> 01:35:06,640
You said yourself that you were at fault.

1003
01:35:08,600 --> 01:35:09,640
Yes.

1004
01:35:09,880 --> 01:35:11,480
Yes, it was just a mistake.

1005
01:35:11,520 --> 01:35:13,360
Don't you ever make mistakes?

1006
01:35:14,160 --> 01:35:15,160
Huh?

1007
01:35:23,040 --> 01:35:25,840
I'm sick
and tired of these despicable insinuations.

1008
01:35:26,440 --> 01:35:28,280
And now, this.

1009
01:35:28,960 --> 01:35:31,280
No one cares about my pride being hurt.

1010
01:35:32,560 --> 01:35:34,000
I care.

1011
01:35:36,840 --> 01:35:38,760
You care, is that so?

1012
01:35:41,560 --> 01:35:43,560
So you didn't hurt my pride at all?

1013
01:35:43,600 --> 01:35:47,480
Didn't you keep hurting me with your words
the more I tried to explain myself?

1014
01:35:49,880 --> 01:35:53,560
You should've acted differently than
the people who are talking about me online.

1015
01:35:55,760 --> 01:36:00,280
You hurt me and you broke
my heart, even though you know who I am.

1016
01:36:04,080 --> 01:36:06,720
The fact that you
still don't trust me after everything

1017
01:36:06,760 --> 01:36:09,600
that happened, everything
we've been through is so hurtful.

1018
01:36:14,440 --> 01:36:16,880
You said I'd face some consequences.

1019
01:36:21,440 --> 01:36:23,720
Even though I didn't do anything wrong.

1020
01:36:25,320 --> 01:36:28,720
But I keep facing consequences ever
since you people came to this house.

1021
01:36:34,480 --> 01:36:38,240
I keep facing consequences for
things I didn't do, crimes I didn't commit.

1022
01:36:44,440 --> 01:36:46,199
Look, I'm sorry about...

1023
01:36:46,200 --> 01:36:50,120
Your being sorry
doesn't change anything, do you understand?

1024
01:36:50,920 --> 01:36:52,480
And I know it never will.

1025
01:36:57,000 --> 01:36:59,040
You said 187 days.

1026
01:37:02,080 --> 01:37:04,200
I'm just waiting for it to end.

1027
01:37:11,720 --> 01:37:13,600
As fast as possible.

1028
01:37:35,120 --> 01:37:37,040
How did I break your heart so bad?

1029
01:38:26,000 --> 01:38:27,160
Haydar.

1030
01:38:28,520 --> 01:38:30,600
We still haven't done anything about Ateş.

1031
01:38:30,640 --> 01:38:32,560
It's like he has nine lives.

1032
01:38:33,520 --> 01:38:35,960
Maybe we need to take one of his lives.

1033
01:38:37,640 --> 01:38:39,600
Did you see the news on Mercan?

1034
01:38:41,680 --> 01:38:42,800
I did.

1035
01:38:43,480 --> 01:38:45,040
It was really cruel.

1036
01:38:46,320 --> 01:38:48,280
Nermin suspects Müzeyyen did it.

1037
01:38:48,600 --> 01:38:52,160
They obviously put someone on her
tail, they're having her followed.

1038
01:38:52,840 --> 01:38:54,600
It could've been Ateş, as well.

1039
01:38:55,840 --> 01:38:57,600
We had a fight over this, too.

1040
01:38:59,000 --> 01:39:00,680
The time has come, now.

1041
01:39:01,440 --> 01:39:02,800
We need to do something.

1042
01:39:03,040 --> 01:39:05,120
We've waited long enough.

1043
01:39:06,040 --> 01:39:07,120
Where to?

1044
01:39:11,240 --> 01:39:12,920
Today is an important day.

1045
01:39:13,360 --> 01:39:15,600
I've got one of the big ones, today.

1046
01:39:15,640 --> 01:39:18,680
I'll find out Ateş' most sensitive secrets.

1047
01:39:21,520 --> 01:39:22,720
We'll see.

1048
01:39:29,880 --> 01:39:30,920
Yes?

1049
01:39:32,400 --> 01:39:33,440
What?

1050
01:39:34,360 --> 01:39:35,560
It's been removed?

1051
01:39:36,360 --> 01:39:37,440
That was fast.

1052
01:39:39,320 --> 01:39:40,600
Okay, I got it.

1053
01:39:43,760 --> 01:39:45,600
Ateş acted fast yet again.

1054
01:39:47,400 --> 01:39:48,880
But I'll act faster.

1055
01:39:48,920 --> 01:39:50,640
I know what to do.

1056
01:39:56,960 --> 01:39:58,040
Hello.

1057
01:39:59,240 --> 01:40:00,960
I have some big news for you.

1058
01:40:01,600 --> 01:40:03,640
It's not just any story, either.

1059
01:40:03,680 --> 01:40:07,520
You'll love it.
You'll be the envy of all other reporters.

1060
01:40:12,400 --> 01:40:13,400
Okay.

1061
01:40:13,440 --> 01:40:15,040
Okay, I'll send it now.

1062
01:40:15,080 --> 01:40:18,400
But you'll
make sure my name isn't mentioned anywhere.

1063
01:40:19,040 --> 01:40:20,080
Okay?

1064
01:40:21,960 --> 01:40:23,160
Okay.

1065
01:40:28,040 --> 01:40:30,520
Let's see if you can stop this, Ateş.

1066
01:40:45,640 --> 01:40:47,320
I will never give up.

1067
01:40:51,080 --> 01:40:53,960
The war is not over until Mercan is mine.

1068
01:42:27,480 --> 01:42:28,760
Ms. Nermin?

1069
01:42:38,040 --> 01:42:39,360
Zehra?

1070
01:42:40,840 --> 01:42:42,960
I was just looking for Ms. Müzeyyen.

1071
01:42:43,400 --> 01:42:44,760
She's not home, I suppose?

1072
01:42:44,800 --> 01:42:47,160
No, she's not home, Ms. Nermin.

1073
01:42:47,680 --> 01:42:48,680
Are you sure?

1074
01:42:49,240 --> 01:42:51,160
I thought I heard her just now.

1075
01:42:51,960 --> 01:42:54,040
That's why I came in here.

1076
01:42:54,720 --> 01:42:56,200
I can wait here, as well.

1077
01:42:56,960 --> 01:42:58,639
I had something to ask her.

1078
01:42:58,640 --> 01:43:00,120
No, they went out.

1079
01:43:00,840 --> 01:43:02,440
Is that so?

1080
01:43:03,960 --> 01:43:08,000
I was just checking to see if she
had any cotton pads, I ran out, you see.

1081
01:43:08,800 --> 01:43:11,199
I can never get my mascara on right.

1082
01:43:11,200 --> 01:43:14,160
Whenever I put it on,
I get it on my eyelids.

1083
01:43:14,200 --> 01:43:16,759
I know what
you mean. I do that all the time, as well.

1084
01:43:16,760 --> 01:43:17,960
I can never get it right.

1085
01:43:18,000 --> 01:43:19,320
Yeah, that happens.

1086
01:43:19,360 --> 01:43:21,720
A
Common evil in the lives of women, I guess.

1087
01:43:22,720 --> 01:43:23,759
Well, then.

1088
01:43:23,760 --> 01:43:26,200
I should leave and get out of your hair.

1089
01:43:26,240 --> 01:43:27,639
Bye, dear.

1090
01:43:27,640 --> 01:43:28,720
Thank you.

1091
01:43:45,640 --> 01:43:47,320
I still can't believe it.

1092
01:43:48,080 --> 01:43:49,960
How could they do something like this?

1093
01:43:51,840 --> 01:43:53,760
He didn't say a word about this, either.

1094
01:43:55,680 --> 01:43:58,320
You're his wife, even
if it's just on paper.

1095
01:43:58,360 --> 01:44:00,600
How could he not say anything?

1096
01:44:02,640 --> 01:44:04,920
He destoryed all trust I had in him in one
go.

1097
01:44:06,680 --> 01:44:08,640
You trusted him?

1098
01:44:09,920 --> 01:44:12,400
When did you start trusting him?

1099
01:44:13,240 --> 01:44:15,680
I... don't know.

1100
01:44:16,400 --> 01:44:18,480
We've been through so much together.

1101
01:44:19,240 --> 01:44:20,920
He did so much for me.

1102
01:44:23,480 --> 01:44:25,080
He saved my life.

1103
01:44:27,120 --> 01:44:30,920
Sometimes, one smile from
him fills you with warmth.

1104
01:44:31,560 --> 01:44:33,840
You think he wouldn't hurt a soul.

1105
01:44:35,520 --> 01:44:38,920
I wanted to believe, somewhere deep
down, that he was a good person.

1106
01:44:40,120 --> 01:44:41,960
But that was obviously a mistake.

1107
01:44:43,040 --> 01:44:44,400
Don't feel bad.

1108
01:44:45,680 --> 01:44:47,560
Everything will be forgotten soon.

1109
01:44:48,240 --> 01:44:50,640
It'll all pass one
day, please don't feel sad, Mercan.

1110
01:45:05,120 --> 01:45:07,360
This social media is an awful space.

1111
01:45:07,400 --> 01:45:09,560
You can muddy the name of someone you don't

1112
01:45:09,600 --> 01:45:11,719
know with a single click, from a distance.

1113
01:45:11,720 --> 01:45:15,280
That's how it works. No one cares about the
truth anymore.

1114
01:45:15,320 --> 01:45:17,960
We believe whatever we see on social media.

1115
01:45:18,000 --> 01:45:19,960
We cancel people without caring if they're

1116
01:45:20,000 --> 01:45:22,200
innocent or not. That's cancel culture for
you.

1117
01:45:22,240 --> 01:45:23,720
Unfortunately.

1118
01:45:24,280 --> 01:45:28,040
But the truth has a
sneaky way of always coming to the surface.

1119
01:45:28,640 --> 01:45:31,536
The people who slandered Ms. Mercan
will recieve their punishment one by one.

1120
01:45:31,560 --> 01:45:36,040
I hope so, Yaşar. I hope Ms. Mercan can rid
herself of this trouble at once.

1121
01:45:37,040 --> 01:45:39,960
We can't let this put our project at risk.

1122
01:45:40,000 --> 01:45:41,600
We still have a lot of work to do.

1123
01:45:44,200 --> 01:45:47,880
I don't think Ms. Mercan
and Mr. Ateş can go on with work

1124
01:45:47,920 --> 01:45:51,559
in this situation. I don't think
they can focus on work.

1125
01:45:51,560 --> 01:45:53,559
That's exactly what I mean.

1126
01:45:53,560 --> 01:45:55,400
We can't let that happen.

1127
01:45:55,440 --> 01:45:57,800
We need to get them motivated as well.

1128
01:45:58,240 --> 01:46:01,520
We need to finish this
art center project as soon as possible.

1129
01:46:01,560 --> 01:46:06,279
The project is as big and prestigious
for the company as it is for us.

1130
01:46:06,280 --> 01:46:09,000
And I'm sure working
will do them some good.

1131
01:46:09,560 --> 01:46:10,480
I'm calling Ms. Mercan.

1132
01:46:10,520 --> 01:46:12,559
I'm going to remind her
we're doing the preview.

1133
01:46:12,560 --> 01:46:14,080
Call her, let's hear what she says.

1134
01:46:14,120 --> 01:46:15,480
Thank you for coming.

1135
01:46:16,000 --> 01:46:17,240
I'm glad I have you.

1136
01:46:17,720 --> 01:46:20,720
You're always here for
me whenever I need you.

1137
01:46:21,080 --> 01:46:24,000
I think that's what friends are for.

1138
01:46:31,840 --> 01:46:32,960
It's Yaşar.

1139
01:46:36,080 --> 01:46:37,240
Yes, Yaşar?

1140
01:46:38,000 --> 01:46:41,280
Ms. Mercan, hello. I wanted to say,

1141
01:46:41,320 --> 01:46:44,679
maybe now is not the best time but

1142
01:46:44,680 --> 01:46:48,399
I wanted to remind you
of this art center project's preview.

1143
01:46:48,400 --> 01:46:51,000
I had emailed you about it. Have you had a

1144
01:46:51,040 --> 01:46:53,959
chance to look at it,
I'm waiting for feedback.

1145
01:46:53,960 --> 01:46:56,279
Uhm,
okay. I don't have my laptop with me right

1146
01:46:56,280 --> 01:46:58,640
now,
but I'll check it at my first availability.

1147
01:46:59,600 --> 01:47:01,280
Okay, thank you very much.

1148
01:47:01,680 --> 01:47:02,680
See you later.

1149
01:47:05,000 --> 01:47:06,839
Sorry I kept you waiting.

1150
01:47:06,840 --> 01:47:08,120
It's okay.

1151
01:47:09,680 --> 01:47:12,880
Mercan, you've been
through difficult things, I know,

1152
01:47:13,360 --> 01:47:15,840
but I also know you're incredibly strong.

1153
01:47:17,880 --> 01:47:19,760
You'll get through this in no time.

1154
01:47:21,440 --> 01:47:22,480
I hope so.

1155
01:47:27,720 --> 01:47:28,720
What happened?

1156
01:47:29,600 --> 01:47:33,080
She said she'd check in a couple
of days. I think we'll be done really soon.

1157
01:47:33,120 --> 01:47:35,239
That's wonderful. That's great news.

1158
01:47:35,240 --> 01:47:35,920
I think so too.

1159
01:47:35,921 --> 01:47:37,080
Yes.

1160
01:47:38,040 --> 01:47:39,080
Wait.

1161
01:47:39,360 --> 01:47:40,520
Let's just shake on it.

1162
01:47:40,560 --> 01:47:41,760
Okay, now we got it.

1163
01:47:44,000 --> 01:47:45,400
Let's keep working then, come on.

1164
01:47:45,440 --> 01:47:46,360
Sure.

1165
01:47:46,400 --> 01:47:49,400
Come on, bring the tapes.
We'll put these up, too.

1166
01:47:49,440 --> 01:47:50,440
Okay.

1167
01:47:52,080 --> 01:47:54,160
These spaces are empty. Here and there.

1168
01:47:55,360 --> 01:47:57,359
Then I'll cut two pieces.

1169
01:47:57,360 --> 01:47:58,679
Our moods just improved.

1170
01:47:58,680 --> 01:48:00,360
Of course, they did!

1171
01:48:41,040 --> 01:48:43,880
I have no one else left to run to but you.

1172
01:48:46,400 --> 01:48:48,000
Please, do something.

1173
01:48:49,640 --> 01:48:52,160
Just one thing to fix everything.

1174
01:49:15,080 --> 01:49:16,200
I don't want it.

1175
01:49:17,840 --> 01:49:19,000
Just take it.

1176
01:49:26,360 --> 01:49:27,720
Thank you.

1177
01:49:30,680 --> 01:49:32,280
I'm sorry about what happened today.

1178
01:49:35,560 --> 01:49:37,440
But I wouldn't do such a thing to you.

1179
01:49:38,560 --> 01:49:39,880
I want you to know that.

1180
01:49:41,600 --> 01:49:42,960
But you kept quiet.

1181
01:49:46,440 --> 01:49:50,720
I would never do
such a thing neither to myself nor to you.

1182
01:49:52,640 --> 01:49:54,640
I'd think about my honor first.

1183
01:49:56,760 --> 01:49:58,280
I don't understand.

1184
01:49:58,960 --> 01:50:01,440
I
Don't understand why this keeps happening.

1185
01:50:02,600 --> 01:50:04,520
But it's starting to feel unbearable.

1186
01:50:07,840 --> 01:50:11,520
I'm trying to remain good despite
everything.

1187
01:50:12,080 --> 01:50:16,760
I'm trying not
to react like them to the evils being done.

1188
01:50:16,800 --> 01:50:21,760
I'm trying to remain kind and remain human
but it's never been harder.

1189
01:50:25,400 --> 01:50:27,000
But I keep trying.

1190
01:50:28,120 --> 01:50:29,800
I have no intention of giving up.

1191
01:50:33,160 --> 01:50:35,720
What happened
today has been really hard on you, I know.

1192
01:50:36,640 --> 01:50:37,760
Very.

1193
01:50:38,520 --> 01:50:39,640
Really hard.

1194
01:50:40,640 --> 01:50:42,480
But it's nothing I can't handle.

1195
01:50:43,080 --> 01:50:44,879
I've handled a lot worse.

1196
01:50:44,880 --> 01:50:47,120
This will pass too, I know.

1197
01:50:52,200 --> 01:50:53,960
You're the one who's actually hurting me.

1198
01:51:08,560 --> 01:51:11,480
My silence doesn't mean I'm not standing by
you.

1199
01:51:12,680 --> 01:51:13,840
But sometimes...

1200
01:51:21,080 --> 01:51:22,360
Hello, Demet?

1201
01:51:22,800 --> 01:51:24,040
Hello, Mercan.

1202
01:51:25,120 --> 01:51:28,520
Another article has just dropped.

1203
01:51:28,880 --> 01:51:30,280
I'm sending you the link.

1204
01:51:31,280 --> 01:51:32,360
Okay.

1205
01:51:32,400 --> 01:51:33,680
I'll check it.

1206
01:51:34,920 --> 01:51:36,080
What is it?

1207
01:51:51,600 --> 01:51:52,840
I can't believe it.

1208
01:51:53,520 --> 01:51:54,760
Let me see.

1209
01:51:59,280 --> 01:52:03,440
"While the rumours of Mercan
Yıldırım and Ateş Karahan's marriage being

1210
01:52:03,480 --> 01:52:08,080
arranged, the photos of her in her black
wedding dress have dropped with a bang.

1211
01:52:11,160 --> 01:52:14,760
"Black swan
Mercan Karahan, is she an unwanted bride?"

1212
01:52:16,000 --> 01:52:18,960
"They're saying Mercan
and Ateş Karahan will get divorced soon."

1213
01:52:25,880 --> 01:52:28,640
Why is this happening? Who's doing this?

1214
01:52:28,680 --> 01:52:32,240
Is it
really so easy to question a woman's honor?

1215
01:52:43,000 --> 01:52:44,080
Don't be upset.

1216
01:52:47,720 --> 01:52:50,000
I'm
going to do whatever it takes to fix this.

1217
01:52:51,560 --> 01:52:52,800
You'll do it, now?

1218
01:53:13,400 --> 01:53:16,120
The queen Zehra keeps declining my calls.

1219
01:53:18,760 --> 01:53:19,920
Hello, Cemal.

1220
01:53:21,360 --> 01:53:22,639
Hi, Berat.

1221
01:53:22,640 --> 01:53:24,680
Mr. Cemal, would you like some tea?

1222
01:53:24,720 --> 01:53:26,240
Sure, I'll have some.

1223
01:53:26,280 --> 01:53:27,720
Come, it's freshly brewed.

1224
01:53:27,760 --> 01:53:29,599
This is yours, go ahead.

1225
01:53:29,600 --> 01:53:30,880
Thank you.

1226
01:53:30,920 --> 01:53:32,000
Go ahead.

1227
01:53:39,160 --> 01:53:40,480
How are you, Mr. Cemal?

1228
01:53:41,400 --> 01:53:42,560
I'm fine, thank you.

1229
01:53:43,720 --> 01:53:47,720
You know me, just
dealing with the garden and whatnot.

1230
01:53:49,560 --> 01:53:52,280
I have a question for you, Mr. Cemal.

1231
01:53:52,800 --> 01:53:55,160
Is it okay if I call you Cemal?

1232
01:53:55,200 --> 01:53:58,640
Why wouldn't it be okay? There's no need to
be on a high horse.

1233
01:53:58,680 --> 01:54:01,080
Thanks, Cemal. You're the best.

1234
01:54:01,120 --> 01:54:05,960
You know,
when you say mister, it sounds so official.

1235
01:54:06,000 --> 01:54:08,240
But I feel close to you.

1236
01:54:09,000 --> 01:54:10,640
That's why.

1237
01:54:14,880 --> 01:54:17,680
So,
Cemal? What's up with you, how's it going?

1238
01:54:18,480 --> 01:54:19,640
Everything's fine.

1239
01:54:19,680 --> 01:54:21,200
It's going well.

1240
01:54:25,240 --> 01:54:27,080
I was just tending to the garden,

1241
01:54:27,880 --> 01:54:31,160
I thought I'd take a tea
break and rest a little.

1242
01:54:31,200 --> 01:54:32,399
Regain my energy.

1243
01:54:32,400 --> 01:54:34,040
So, you took a tea break.

1244
01:54:34,080 --> 01:54:36,040
You gave me your tea, go get yourself one.

1245
01:54:36,080 --> 01:54:39,800
Oh, it's no problem. I'll
get it whenever, it's just tea. It's fine.

1246
01:54:39,840 --> 01:54:41,040
You enjoy.

1247
01:54:41,080 --> 01:54:42,160
Thanks.

1248
01:54:45,240 --> 01:54:48,400
The weather's getting
really cold too, don't you think,

1249
01:54:48,440 --> 01:54:51,440
Cemal? I saw on the
news, my hometown's getting snow.

1250
01:54:53,440 --> 01:54:55,320
You're not from here,
either, are you, Cemal?

1251
01:54:55,920 --> 01:54:57,440
No, I'm not.

1252
01:54:57,720 --> 01:54:59,440
You're not.

1253
01:55:04,360 --> 01:55:05,760
Is your family at your hometown?

1254
01:55:10,400 --> 01:55:11,560
Family?

1255
01:55:13,560 --> 01:55:14,640
I don't have one.

1256
01:55:22,160 --> 01:55:23,760
I figured you out, Cemal.

1257
01:55:24,360 --> 01:55:26,320
You're a lone wolf, right?

1258
01:55:26,760 --> 01:55:30,920
That's the best. Being
your own master is surely the best.

1259
01:55:31,120 --> 01:55:32,160
That's great.

1260
01:55:32,200 --> 01:55:33,080
It is.

1261
01:55:33,120 --> 01:55:34,240
Surely.

1262
01:55:36,000 --> 01:55:37,120
I should get going.

1263
01:55:39,840 --> 01:55:43,919
I really enjoyed chatting
with you. We should do this more often.

1264
01:55:43,920 --> 01:55:46,520
We had a deep talk and everything. Was that
not nice?

1265
01:55:47,440 --> 01:55:49,240
Okay, we'll do that.

1266
01:55:56,400 --> 01:55:58,239
He's so mysterious. I
could not pry anything

1267
01:55:58,240 --> 01:55:59,920
out of him no matter how hard if I tried.

1268
01:56:01,000 --> 01:56:03,080
He's so secretive. I did all the talking.

1269
01:56:05,160 --> 01:56:06,239
Anyway.

1270
01:56:06,240 --> 01:56:07,360
Berat!

1271
01:56:09,120 --> 01:56:10,360
Can we talk?

1272
01:56:21,200 --> 01:56:22,360
He has every right.

1273
01:56:23,400 --> 01:56:25,400
I
Made a mistake staying silent for so long.

1274
01:56:26,000 --> 01:56:28,200
I haven't said a word about my family, yet.

1275
01:56:29,160 --> 01:56:31,520
I'm hiding my
family, yet I go and ask for Çiçek's hand?

1276
01:56:32,080 --> 01:56:33,800
Of course they don't approve.

1277
01:56:35,120 --> 01:56:36,640
They don't know you at all.

1278
01:56:38,400 --> 01:56:39,440
This won't do.

1279
01:56:39,880 --> 01:56:42,560
I need to tell these people the truth.

1280
01:56:59,160 --> 01:57:00,440
I brought us coffee.

1281
01:57:02,360 --> 01:57:03,400
Yeah?

1282
01:57:04,680 --> 01:57:05,800
Thanks.

1283
01:57:12,920 --> 01:57:15,280
Is
There something you want to tell me, Burak?

1284
01:57:18,000 --> 01:57:22,160
Uhm... I wanted to tell you...

1285
01:57:23,360 --> 01:57:24,680
What did you want to say?

1286
01:57:26,360 --> 01:57:28,400
Well, I wanted to say...

1287
01:57:29,280 --> 01:57:33,320
I'll get photocopies of
these and bring them right back.

1288
01:57:41,320 --> 01:57:43,400
Burak must've already ended it in his mind.

1289
01:57:55,040 --> 01:57:56,200
They still haven't shown up.

1290
01:57:57,440 --> 01:57:59,440
They just went shopping,
they'll be back soon.

1291
01:58:00,520 --> 01:58:02,239
It's better they don't come if you're

1292
01:58:02,240 --> 01:58:03,800
going to greet them in such anger.

1293
01:58:04,280 --> 01:58:05,600
I just don't get it, Cemal.

1294
01:58:07,240 --> 01:58:08,840
I keep talking but they don't listen.

1295
01:58:10,840 --> 01:58:12,200
I've just had another talk.

1296
01:58:12,880 --> 01:58:14,479
It's as if they're doing it in spite.

1297
01:58:14,480 --> 01:58:18,080
Maybe it wasn't Ms. Müzeyyen's
doing, why execute with extreme prejudice?

1298
01:58:18,840 --> 01:58:20,200
Anyone may have had the pictures.

1299
01:58:20,240 --> 01:58:22,720
When Mercan
became the new hot topic, they released it.

1300
01:58:23,560 --> 01:58:26,000
People are cruel, that's the era
we live in.

1301
01:58:29,880 --> 01:58:31,560
Ateş, could you just sit down?

1302
01:58:31,960 --> 01:58:34,360
You can't walk around
like a madman everytime you get angry.

1303
01:58:34,400 --> 01:58:36,960
I
Feel nauseous and dizzy just watching you.

1304
01:58:38,720 --> 01:58:41,200
This does neither you nor Mercan any good.

1305
01:58:42,600 --> 01:58:45,800
I talked to the lawyer, he's going to have
the pictures removed by tomorrow.

1306
01:58:46,320 --> 01:58:48,400
No
One will even remember by tomorrow, anyway.

1307
01:58:48,440 --> 01:58:49,800
Suit yourself.

1308
01:58:57,320 --> 01:58:58,680
That's not the point.

1309
01:59:01,120 --> 01:59:02,960
I don't care what anyone thinks.

1310
01:59:07,200 --> 01:59:11,880
Knowing the truth but
not being able to say anything is so hard.

1311
01:59:14,800 --> 01:59:16,880
She thought I had something to do with it.

1312
01:59:22,600 --> 01:59:26,880
She
looks into my eyes and waits for an answer.

1313
01:59:28,320 --> 01:59:31,440
The only thing I can give her is silence.

1314
01:59:36,040 --> 01:59:37,800
I know this hurts her.

1315
01:59:41,920 --> 01:59:43,680
But there's nothing I can do.

1316
01:59:48,720 --> 01:59:51,320
I have to keep silent to protect the people
I love.

1317
01:59:56,320 --> 01:59:58,600
But seeing her so upset,

1318
02:00:01,280 --> 02:00:03,280
breaks my heart into pieces.

1319
02:00:04,160 --> 02:00:05,560
It's like I can't breathe.

1320
02:00:05,600 --> 02:00:07,080
Stop talking like that.

1321
02:00:08,360 --> 02:00:09,360
It'll pass.

1322
02:00:09,400 --> 02:00:10,880
Everything will be okay, don't worry.

1323
02:00:14,480 --> 02:00:15,520
I hope so.

1324
02:00:16,840 --> 02:00:18,320
I hope so but,

1325
02:00:19,400 --> 02:00:21,360
they don't allow me moment of peace.

1326
02:00:28,080 --> 02:00:30,920
We're going to have a family
portrait taken today, you remember, right?

1327
02:00:32,720 --> 02:00:34,320
A family portrait, huh?

1328
02:00:37,280 --> 02:00:38,600
What kind of a family is this?

1329
02:00:40,040 --> 02:00:41,640
No one listens to each other.

1330
02:00:43,480 --> 02:00:45,240
Ms. Müzeyyen told me to tell

1331
02:00:45,280 --> 02:00:47,360
you we need to be ready by noon.

1332
02:00:50,720 --> 02:00:52,520
Everything will be okay, don't worry.

1333
02:00:53,880 --> 02:00:55,080
I'm going to get ready.

1334
02:01:43,560 --> 02:01:45,120
What are you doing in my room?

1335
02:01:45,680 --> 02:01:46,880
I was waiting for you.

1336
02:01:47,560 --> 02:01:49,120
You can't come in without permission.

1337
02:01:50,040 --> 02:01:52,120
I won't stay long, don't worry.

1338
02:01:55,160 --> 02:01:57,520
Your mask of innocence has finally fallen.

1339
02:02:00,720 --> 02:02:02,880
Everyone will see what kind of a person you
are.

1340
02:02:03,600 --> 02:02:04,880
They already have.

1341
02:02:05,680 --> 02:02:07,840
Did you enjoy watching me get slandered?

1342
02:02:08,520 --> 02:02:09,679
I did.

1343
02:02:09,680 --> 02:02:11,040
I always will.

1344
02:02:11,920 --> 02:02:13,800
And how do we know it's false?

1345
02:02:16,000 --> 02:02:17,400
You did this.

1346
02:02:19,360 --> 02:02:21,679
You gave the press those pictures.

1347
02:02:21,680 --> 02:02:23,040
You and your mom.

1348
02:02:23,560 --> 02:02:26,120
Well done! You clever girl.

1349
02:02:27,760 --> 02:02:29,560
It wasn't that hard to guess.

1350
02:02:30,400 --> 02:02:32,760
Who else could be so evil?

1351
02:02:37,280 --> 02:02:40,920
I mean, I really don't understand why.

1352
02:02:42,640 --> 02:02:45,680
Why are you so evil, why do you hate me so
much?

1353
02:02:47,120 --> 02:02:48,760
Because you deserve it.

1354
02:02:50,240 --> 02:02:52,920
A shameless and depraved woman like

1355
02:02:52,960 --> 02:02:55,480
yourself deserves so much worse.

1356
02:03:11,000 --> 02:03:14,160
We should've done so much
worse, do you hear me?

1357
02:03:15,000 --> 02:03:15,760
You deserve-

1358
02:03:15,800 --> 02:03:17,040
What's going on here?

1359
02:03:18,040 --> 02:03:19,280
Ateş.

1360
02:03:19,320 --> 02:03:21,320
Did you see how she slapped me?

1361
02:03:22,240 --> 02:03:23,360
I did.

1362
02:03:26,600 --> 02:03:27,840
And I saw why.

1363
02:03:32,560 --> 02:03:34,200
Get out of here, Aslı.

1364
02:03:36,080 --> 02:03:36,560
But-

1365
02:03:36,600 --> 02:03:37,680
Aslı!

1366
02:03:39,000 --> 02:03:40,160
Get out.

1367
02:03:43,600 --> 02:03:45,600
Don't you ever get anywhere near
Mercan again.

1368
02:04:03,320 --> 02:04:04,360
Are you okay?

1369
02:04:06,720 --> 02:04:07,800
I knew.

1370
02:04:08,920 --> 02:04:09,960
Knew what?

1371
02:04:12,520 --> 02:04:14,880
I knew you
were keeping silent to protect your family.

1372
02:04:18,280 --> 02:04:21,400
I waited for you to tell me yourself but

1373
02:04:22,240 --> 02:04:24,080
I knew very well you wouldn't say anything.

1374
02:04:26,880 --> 02:04:28,120
I knew, too.

1375
02:04:30,080 --> 02:04:31,840
From the very beginning.

1376
02:04:32,760 --> 02:04:33,920
Knew what?

1377
02:04:34,920 --> 02:04:36,400
That you were innocent.

1378
02:04:47,480 --> 02:04:49,761
I'm going to ask you for something if it's
okay with you.

1379
02:05:10,240 --> 02:05:11,480
Malik dares to talk to me.

1380
02:05:11,520 --> 02:05:13,840
He dares to show up still, what a shameless
guy.

1381
02:05:18,320 --> 02:05:20,080
Mom, what happened? Are you okay?

1382
02:05:21,440 --> 02:05:25,600
Son, we
need to pay back Malik as soon as possible.

1383
02:05:25,640 --> 02:05:31,640
We'll put all our
wages toward that if we have to.

1384
02:05:31,680 --> 02:05:33,599
It's not a small amount.

1385
02:05:33,600 --> 02:05:38,400
Don't say Malik to me, mom. I feel on edge
when I hear his name.

1386
02:05:39,960 --> 02:05:41,200
Let's stop talking about him.

1387
02:05:44,280 --> 02:05:46,280
He keeps talking even if you don't.

1388
02:05:46,320 --> 02:05:50,840
He came to talk to me, he said he wouldn't
go back to Egypt if he married Çiçek.

1389
02:05:51,920 --> 02:05:54,440
God, give me
patience! He's still going on about Çiçek?

1390
02:05:54,480 --> 02:05:55,520
Huh?

1391
02:05:55,560 --> 02:05:57,399
Son, calm down.

1392
02:05:57,400 --> 02:05:59,680
Sit back
down. I'm telling you what he said.

1393
02:06:01,840 --> 02:06:02,879
Okay, I'm calm.

1394
02:06:02,880 --> 02:06:05,160
Calm down, Berat. Calm down.

1395
02:06:05,840 --> 02:06:07,776
I'm calm. What did you
say? What did you tell him?

1396
02:06:07,800 --> 02:06:09,480
I didn't say anything.

1397
02:06:10,760 --> 02:06:14,560
Look, mom. Don't you get all emotional and
fall for it.

1398
02:06:15,560 --> 02:06:16,960
Son, I told you I said nothing.

1399
02:06:20,520 --> 02:06:25,800
Both Malik and
Çiçek went behind our backs and fooled us.

1400
02:06:27,000 --> 02:06:28,319
We're not falling for it.

1401
02:06:28,320 --> 02:06:30,399
Son, I told you I didn't.

1402
02:06:30,400 --> 02:06:31,680
There's no way.

1403
02:06:31,720 --> 02:06:33,920
There won't
be any talk of Malik in this house anymore.

1404
02:06:33,960 --> 02:06:36,080
It's not so easy to marry my daughter.

1405
02:06:36,120 --> 02:06:37,120
Of course.

1406
02:06:38,320 --> 02:06:40,560
We need to pay him back first.

1407
02:06:46,520 --> 02:06:47,720
I'm going to handle it.

1408
02:06:48,560 --> 02:06:50,760
Son, when you say things like "I'm

1409
02:06:50,800 --> 02:06:52,919
going to handle it." I get scared.

1410
02:06:52,920 --> 02:06:54,240
Don't you go to loan-

1411
02:06:54,280 --> 02:06:57,040
Okay, mom. Okay. Don't say that.

1412
02:06:58,080 --> 02:06:59,480
I made that mistake once.

1413
02:07:00,320 --> 02:07:01,840
I'm on the right path now.

1414
02:07:02,680 --> 02:07:04,720
If you say so. Be careful.

1415
02:07:06,800 --> 02:07:08,320
I'll handle it one way or another.

1416
02:07:21,200 --> 02:07:22,120
Stop!

1417
02:07:22,160 --> 02:07:23,840
Stop, don't run, Fatih!

1418
02:07:23,880 --> 02:07:25,120
Stop!

1419
02:07:40,320 --> 02:07:41,520
I told you to stop.

1420
02:07:43,840 --> 02:07:45,440
Stop running, Fatih!

1421
02:07:58,320 --> 02:07:59,320
Fatih, stop.

1422
02:08:02,400 --> 02:08:03,600
I'll shoot!

1423
02:08:15,920 --> 02:08:17,480
I've been watching you for a while.

1424
02:08:18,360 --> 02:08:20,480
I'm aware you've been spying on me.

1425
02:08:21,520 --> 02:08:23,479
If you want to get out
of this alive, you'll

1426
02:08:23,480 --> 02:08:25,200
tell me everything you know about Ateş.

1427
02:08:26,600 --> 02:08:27,800
I don't know anything.

1428
02:08:28,320 --> 02:08:29,720
Shoot me all you'd like.

1429
02:08:29,760 --> 02:08:31,639
You obviously don't care for your life.

1430
02:08:31,640 --> 02:08:32,999
What about your family?

1431
02:08:33,000 --> 02:08:35,240
Your mom, dad? Your wife and children?

1432
02:08:36,040 --> 02:08:38,440
Will you be able to give up their lives so
easily?

1433
02:08:38,480 --> 02:08:40,600
Would you like me to shoot them in
their head?

1434
02:08:40,640 --> 02:08:41,640
Huh!?

1435
02:08:45,360 --> 02:08:47,239
Tell me your answer.

1436
02:08:47,240 --> 02:08:49,240
Talk! Who's this Ateş?

1437
02:08:54,160 --> 02:08:56,239
I told you what I'll do if you don't talk.

1438
02:08:56,240 --> 02:08:57,480
Tell me!

1439
02:08:57,520 --> 02:09:00,360
Doesn't he have any
relatives, anyone who knows him?

1440
02:09:01,960 --> 02:09:04,160
He had a sister.

1441
02:09:04,240 --> 02:09:05,279
She died.

1442
02:09:05,280 --> 02:09:06,440
Her name...

1443
02:09:07,640 --> 02:09:09,000
He never said.

1444
02:09:09,040 --> 02:09:11,240
I don't know when or how she died.

1445
02:09:12,160 --> 02:09:13,680
Doesn't he have any other family?

1446
02:09:14,200 --> 02:09:15,320
I don't know.

1447
02:09:15,360 --> 02:09:16,759
What do you mean you don't know!?

1448
02:09:16,760 --> 02:09:18,599
An uncle, an aunt, anything!

1449
02:09:18,600 --> 02:09:20,520
Did storks fly him down?

1450
02:09:21,560 --> 02:09:23,040
If he has any, I don't know.

1451
02:09:35,560 --> 02:09:36,760
Damn it!

1452
02:09:38,040 --> 02:09:39,279
Come here!

1453
02:09:39,280 --> 02:09:40,520
Don't run!

1454
02:09:53,760 --> 02:09:55,800
Don't run! Where are you?

1455
02:10:13,480 --> 02:10:14,560
Damn it.

1456
02:10:15,960 --> 02:10:17,040
Damn it.

1457
02:10:17,840 --> 02:10:19,239
Damn it!

1458
02:10:19,240 --> 02:10:20,840
I missed him.

1459
02:10:29,600 --> 02:10:30,880
Çiçek?

1460
02:10:30,920 --> 02:10:32,600
Are you okay?

1461
02:10:37,080 --> 02:10:39,440
I can't stand to see you like this.

1462
02:10:41,240 --> 02:10:43,920
Mom won't let us get married, Malik.

1463
02:10:43,960 --> 02:10:46,640
Just wait, don't lose your hope, now.

1464
02:10:46,680 --> 02:10:48,840
I trust Ms. Binnaz.

1465
02:10:49,520 --> 02:10:51,240
She'll see reason, soon.

1466
02:10:51,600 --> 02:10:53,480
I'm telling you now, you'll see.

1467
02:10:54,960 --> 02:10:57,000
She's only stalling us, that's all.

1468
02:10:57,040 --> 02:10:58,720
How do you know?

1469
02:10:58,760 --> 02:11:00,920
I heard her talking to Berat.

1470
02:11:04,080 --> 02:11:07,120
Still, I trust her.

1471
02:11:08,320 --> 02:11:11,879
Look, the only thing we need is time.

1472
02:11:11,880 --> 02:11:13,640
In time, everything will be fine.

1473
02:11:14,640 --> 02:11:16,040
We don't have the time.

1474
02:11:16,080 --> 02:11:17,640
I know there isn't.

1475
02:11:18,240 --> 02:11:21,639
Çiçek, you're obviously very upset.

1476
02:11:21,640 --> 02:11:24,279
If you want, we
can go out and stroll around a little bit.

1477
02:11:24,280 --> 02:11:25,879
It'd do both you and me some good.

1478
02:11:25,880 --> 02:11:26,720
Huh?

1479
02:11:26,760 --> 02:11:28,320
How will I go out, Malik?

1480
02:11:28,360 --> 02:11:30,159
How will I leave the house?

1481
02:11:30,160 --> 02:11:33,040
I have to report each step I take to them.

1482
02:11:33,680 --> 02:11:37,080
They watch my every move and interrogate my
every word.

1483
02:11:37,120 --> 02:11:38,840
It's so hard.

1484
02:11:39,600 --> 02:11:41,080
And what's my crime?

1485
02:11:42,800 --> 02:11:44,520
Loving you.

1486
02:11:52,840 --> 02:11:54,040
My beautiful girlfriend.

1487
02:11:55,840 --> 02:11:56,880
Malik.

1488
02:11:57,600 --> 02:12:00,400
If we stay here, we can never be together.

1489
02:12:02,440 --> 02:12:04,000
What can we do, Çiçek?

1490
02:12:07,160 --> 02:12:08,600
Let's just go.

1491
02:12:08,640 --> 02:12:09,920
Let's run away.

1492
02:12:16,160 --> 02:12:19,120
We have
no other choice, if we want to be together.

1493
02:12:26,680 --> 02:12:28,040
Please, Malik.

1494
02:12:28,080 --> 02:12:31,160
Let's run away, get married and be happy.

1495
02:12:55,520 --> 02:12:58,440
Where is Ateş, guys? It's almost time.

1496
02:12:58,480 --> 02:13:00,760
He was getting ready,
Ms. Müzeyyen. He'll be here soon.

1497
02:13:00,800 --> 02:13:01,840
Okay, then.

1498
02:13:01,880 --> 02:13:05,039
Let's go get a couple
shots in until he comes.

1499
02:13:05,040 --> 02:13:06,120
Okay, then.

1500
02:14:12,960 --> 02:14:14,720
What is she doing here?

1501
02:14:19,200 --> 02:14:21,440
Mr. Ateş, go in the middle with your wife.

1502
02:14:21,480 --> 02:14:23,520
Mr. Cemal, you should step closer.

1503
02:14:42,160 --> 02:14:44,640
This was supposed to be a family portrait.

1504
02:14:48,680 --> 02:14:49,960
It is.

1505
02:14:52,360 --> 02:14:53,960
We're together as a family.

1506
02:15:17,000 --> 02:15:19,960
If everyone's ready, I'm going to take it.
Everyone, smile.

1507
02:15:30,240 --> 02:15:31,560
Smile.

1508
02:15:36,440 --> 02:15:39,720
You don't want
to be sulking in a family portrait, do you?

1509
02:15:56,400 --> 02:15:59,320
That's it.
You look great. Hold that pose, I have it.
